title: summer and eddie's red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake, flour, cocoa powder and baking soda.
In another bowl mix with a beater the sugar, vanilla and butter; then add eggs, one at a time.
Add food coloring and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients in well.
Then pour both bowls of mixture into one.
Finally, add buttermilk.
Melt cream cheese and mix into the ingredients well. Pour batter into three 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° until done (check with toothpick).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter, add flour and stir.
When a little thick, add scalded milk and salt.
Pour over potatoes.

title: meal-in-one-dish
directions: Combine beef, salt, pepper and onion.
Heat skillet and add beef mixture.
Cook until done and brown.
Add tomatoes and stir in macaroni.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Add Seven-Up to jello.
Let set until almost jelled.
Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water in a 2-quart microproof bowl.
Add 1 1/4 cups of the sugar, hot water and salt.
Blend well.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on High 6 to 7 minutes or until mixture is thick and clear.
Stir occasionally.
Set aside. Beat egg yolks in another bowl until thick.
Gradually beat into cornstarch mixture.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Blend in lemon juice and peel.
Pour into pie crust.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in a large bowl until foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining sugar until whites are stiff and glassy.
Blend in vanilla. Spread over cooled filling, sealing the edges.
Heat in conventional oven to 450° for 4 to 6 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip chess squares
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chocolate chip dough.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour over dough and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: dipped peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of the crackers.
Top with other half to form sandwich.
Refrigerate until chocolate is ready. Melt chocolate chips and shortening over warm water.
Stir until smooth.
Dip sandwiches and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate again until chocolate has hardened.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Pour over 1 loaf cubed bread and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco seasoned salad
directions: Mix together taco seasoning mix, sour cream and cream cheese. Put mixture on large platter.
Cut up lettuce and put on top of mixture.
Add tomatoes and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Dip and eat on taco chips.

title: rich spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry bacon; drain on paper towels.
Set aside.
Add onion to drippings; saute, adding hamburger and cooking until no longer pink.
Drain off drippings and add remaining ingredients, cooking until desired consistency, adding garlic cloves halfway through cooking.
Add bacon (crushed) back into sauce when done.

title: jim's little pizzas
directions: Cut muffins into 2 halves.
Prepare as many as you want according to your appetite.
Toast lightly in broiler.
Spread 1 teaspoon oil on each 1/2 muffin.
Spread 1 tablespoon (more or less) to cover muffin completely.
Sprinkle oregano lightly.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese melts, approximately 2 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs, lemon juice, onions and mustard.
Fold in crab.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: dessert au riz
directions: Soak raisins in hot water to cover until raisins are soft. In a double boiler, heat milk and rice.
Beat egg yolks until smooth and add brown sugar and salt.
Add milk and rice mixture very slowly, then pour back into double boiler and cook over boiling water until very thick.
Fold in egg whites.
Add vanilla or lemon juice.
Fold in drained raisins.
Serve warm or cold or with fruit (blueberries and a sprinkle of cinnamon).

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place roll dough in 9 x 13-inch baking pan to form a crust. Beat egg and cream and pour over crust.
Brown and drain crumbled sausage and sprinkle along with diced, cooked ham over egg mixture.
Top with cheeses and bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes. (Can be prepared night before and refrigerated until baking time.)

title: texas-style chili
directions: In deep pan, heat oil and brown meat well; add garlic, celery and onions.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, spices, seasonings and beans.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 90 minutes, depending on desired consistency.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Mix undiluted soups thoroughly; add 1/4 cup cheese.
Mix in broccoli and chicken (cut into chunks).
Top with remaining buttered crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and browned.

title: corn souffle
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix both cans of corn, butter, milk, flour and sugar.
Beat eggs until light.
Add to corn mixture. Turn into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until center is firm.

title: fruit slice
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat in chocolate.
Add sifted dry ingredients in thirds, alternately with the milk and flavoring, beating until smooth after each addition. Stir in nuts.
Using 2 buttered jelly roll pans, spoon batter in 4 rows, the length of the pans (2 rows in each pan).
Arrange batter together in nice even strips, about 2-inches wide.
Beat egg white with fork and brush some over each row, being careful not to spill over onto pan.
Sprinkle some sugar lightly over top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Frost if you wish.
Cut in diagonal slices.
Makes about 36 slices.

title: english muffins
directions: Divide dough in half.
Turn 1 portion of dough out onto a smooth surface heavily sprinkled with cornmeal.
Pat dough into a circle 1/2-inch thick, using palms of hands.
Cut dough into rounds using a 2 3/4-inch cutter.	Cut carefully as leftover dough should not be used.
Repeat procedure.
Sprinkle 2 baking sheets with cornmeal.
Transfer dough rounds to baking sheets, placing 2-inches apart with cornmeal side down.
One side should remain free of cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a draft free place (85°) 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Using a wide spatula, transfer to a preheated, lightly greased electric skillet (360°).
Place rounds, cornmeal side down in skillet; cook 5 to 6 minutes or until brown.
Turn and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into a ball. Roll in crushed nuts. Chill overnight.

title: easy stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan. Simmer about 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: orange jello salad with topping
directions: Prepare Jell-O using 2 cups boiling water and only 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Reserve juice from pineapple and orange segments.
If juice does not amount to 1 cup, add enough water to make 1 cup liquid for the topping.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1/3 cup lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar together.
Set aside.

title: dink's lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal in a bowl.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and beat with hand or mixer until smooth.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325° or until top is golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with a spoon to blend, then beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pans instead of tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes and test for doneness.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayo.
Spread on crescent rolls.
Top with favorite veggies.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: You will need wide mouth canning jars.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with milk.
(Add baking powder with flour.)
Add nuts last.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove skin; boil chicken in salted water for approximately 1 hour or until tender.
Remove, let cool and pick from bone into small pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well and cut up.
Arrange broccoli in a lightly greased casserole dish; top with chicken.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil in large bowl.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla extract and cinnamon.
Mix by hand.
Add apples and nuts.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan generously.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with a wire whisk, combine the first 6 ingredients .
Pour filling into pie crust. Bake for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: lemon bars(makes 24 bars)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: island cucumbers in vinegar
directions: In a saucepan, combine the vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Let the mixture cool.
Place in a glass jar with a lid and chill in refrigerator for an hour before using. Cut cucumbers into very thin slices; do not peel.
Add to vinegar solution.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie with pecan crust
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream in large bowl until smooth. Gradually add sugar and beat until blended; add eggs, one at a time, beating just to blend after each addition.
Transfer 1/3 cup cheese mixture to small bowl; set aside.
Add pumpkin and spices to remaining cheese mixture and beat until blended.
Spread in crust.
Drop reserved 1/3 cup cheese mixture by teaspoon over filling.
With tip of sharp knife gently swirl in decorative pattern.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375° or until filling is firm. Cool on rack; cover and chill.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Chill until syrupy. Blend with chilled jello pudding, cottage cheese, pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: chili and rice casserole
directions: Spread chili
on
bottom
of
an 8-inch casserole dish. Spoon rice on
top
of chili. Blend muffin mix, cheese, pepper and milk. Layer over
rice. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: oyster cracker snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir occasionally for approximately one hour, until blended well.
Store in airtight container.

title: large layer cake, thrifty pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beginning and ending with flour, alternate flour and buttermilk into butter, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla.
Line layer pans with waxed paper, greasing pan with butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 regular or 8 thin layers.
Can be used for two layer cakes.

title: fat-free applesauce cake
directions: May use 3/4 cup of nuts if desired; of course, no longer fat free.

title: barbecue style sirloin tip
directions: Rub meat surface with garlic if desired.
To marinate, place roast in plastic bag; set in deep bowl.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat; close bag.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.

title: maple syrup cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar. Stir well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

Blend in maple syrup gradually. Sift dry ingredients. Add hot water alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients (with electric mixer, use low speed).
Pour into an oblong pan which has been well-greased and floured or two 8-inch round layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: southern cheese salad
directions: Whip and cream together the first four ingredients.
Next blend the cheese mixture into the fruit mixture.
Fold in one cup whipped topping.
Freeze.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Mix together next four ingredients and add to first mixture.
Fold in coconut, pecans and apples.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300° in pan with hole in center (angel food pan).

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine and cook gently until done.
Add 8 ounces shredded cheese with 1 tablespoon flour.
Simmer and serve.

title: mojo criollo(creole garlic sauce)
directions: Using a food processor or mortar and pestle, crush the garlic with salt to form a thick paste.
In a mixing bowl, combine the garlic paste, onion and juice and let the mixture set at room temperature for 30 minutes or longer.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Fry bacon till half-way cooked.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts.
Hold together with toothpicks.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Now clean out the refrigerator.
You can add cooked rice and macaroni, leftover beans or other vegetables.
Also you need more canned large tomatoes and 2 cans tomato sauce, depending on your taste.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake in cubes.

title: overnite slaw
directions: Grate up cabbage and place in a bowl with lid.
Add remaining ingredients and stir, then place lid on.
Set out at room temperature overnight.

title: carrot cake 14 karat frosting
directions: Cream together the butter, cheese and vanilla.
Add the powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.

title: alaskan jerky
directions: Marinate venison in glass container 8 to 12 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and place in pan in 150° oven for 12 hours. You can lay meat on a cookie sheet, but drain off liquid as needed.
(Be sure not to fill jar too full when marinating.)
Good to munch on while sitting in a tree stand all day waiting for that next deer.

title: minnesota pickles
directions: Put cukes, onions and peppers in a gallon jar, alternating layers.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cold vegetables in jar.
Will be ready in 12 hours.

title: orange nog
directions: Blend all ingredients 1 minute on high.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Stick whole cloves 1/2-inch apart.
Place in baking dish with little water.
Bake in slow 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Heat cider with stick of cinnamon to boiling.
Add brandy and rum flavoring to suit taste.

title: blackberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve
packages
blackberry jello with juice from pineapple and
juice
from blueberries.
Let thicken, then add can of	blueberries
and
can of crushed pineapple.
Spread in pan with blended cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: eggs and sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until puffed high and brown.

title: swiss beans
directions: Melt oleo in skillet over low heat.
Add onion; brown lightly. Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine sauce and beans; pour into dish.
Sprinkle with nuts before serving.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza spread
directions: Layer ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: creamy southern fried corn
directions: Heat bacon grease in frying pan over medium heat.
When its hot, add corn and lower heat.
Stir in flour, sugar, milk and water.
Mix well and cook gently until nice and tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
You may need to add a touch more milk if too dry.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on 1 slice of bread.
Spread jelly on other slice.
Press 2 slices together and enjoy.

title: salmon patties
directions: In bowl, mix together salmon, crackers, egg, salt and pepper, breaking up the salmon well.
Shape salmon mixture into 5 patties, using about 1/2 cup of mixture for each. Make sure they are firm.

title: "bethunes" sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, salt and nutmeg in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until creamy.
Add sweet potatoes; beat until well blended.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Pour filling into pastry shells, using about 4 cups in each shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and onion.
Add all ingredients (except dressing mix).
Pour into long casserole dish.
Spread dressing mix on top and spread thinly with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Season meat with Lawry's seasoned salt and pepper.
Brown meat in skillet.
Put cabbage in the bottom of a casserole.
Add a layer of rice; add meat.
Pour soup over all.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's spoon bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, salt and butter.
Cook into a mush.
Add egg yolks.
Beat until light.
Stir in egg whites, beaten stiff. Pour in greased casserole and set in pan of water and bake.
It takes about 45 minutes to bake in a rather hot oven.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until well done; drain and mash.
Add vanilla, salt and 10x sugar.
Keep adding sugar until stiff enough to roll on sugared surface.
When rolled out, spread peanut butter over top.
Roll up like jelly roll and slice.

title: cornish game hens
directions: Rinse birds; rub with black pepper and garlic powder or seasoned salt with rosemary and basil.
Put 1/2 cloves and ginger in cavity of birds.
Place birds in rack inside iron skillet or heavy pan.
(I like birds crisp, so I cook them above sauce; Teflon rack is ideal.)

title: perfect roast beef(well done ends; rare center)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place seasoned roast, uncovered, in oven for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and do not open oven door.
Forty minutes before serving, turn oven on.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: In skillet, in hot
oil,
cook	chicken about 2 minutes with garlic; add onions,
broccoli
and	green
peppers.
Cook until tender but crisp.
Stir
in
soup,	water and soy sauce. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: old fashioned apple butter
directions: Cook quartered apples in water until soft.
Put through a food mill or sieve and measure to make 16 cups.
Put in a large kettle and add other ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring often, about 1 1/2 hours.
Butter should turn a deep reddish brown and thicken into a smooth mass.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: garlic butter
directions: Beat melted butter and crushed garlic together in a blender. Brush on bread and heat.

title: strawberry and banana dream
directions: In large bowl, mix pie filling, cream cheese (softened) and Cool Whip until blended well.
Add sliced strawberries and sliced bananas and two cups vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate immediately. Makes 12 servings.

title: refrigerated sweet pickles
directions: In a large kettle, mix the sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric and mustard seed. Stir often. Bring to a boil. Fill jars with cucumber-onion mix.
Toss this in bowl beforehand.
After in jars, put in boiling mixture. When cool, put on lids and refrigerate. This can be kept for months in refrigerator.
Let stand 3 days before eating.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix and cook, stirring constantly; cook until it forms a firm ball when dropped in water.
When cooked enough, add the vanilla and beat until it seems like cold molasses in winter.
Pour into buttered pan.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Add egg and soup.
Mix and add chopped onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and stuffing.
Place in lightly greased casserole and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pink elephant punch
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
Combine all ingredients.
Add ice ring just before serving.
Yields 48 servings.

title: banana berry brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Mix brownie mix, water, oil and 1 egg until blended.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan (or tart pan).
Bake 25 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, 1 egg and vanilla at medium speed until blended.
Pour over brownie crust.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Cool and top with fruit. Drizzle with chocolate.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Fill the cooled pie shell with a layer of tomatoes and onions. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and chives.
Layer again. Combine mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese; spread on top, sealing all edges.
(Optional:
May sprinkle top with crushed bacon and Parmesan.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: trifle
directions: For best results, make this at least a few hours before serving.
Cut cake into 1 inch squares and sprinkle with liquor.

title: strawberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cover strawberries with 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Cook until thick the sugar, water and cornstarch. Remove from heat. Add strawberry jello. Mix well. Cool. Pour over strawberries. Then pour into pie shell. Refrigerate. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cherry delight
directions: Whip
egg
whites stiff.
Fold in cream of tartar.
Add sugar in small amounts.
Fold in cracker crumbs, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Bake
in ungreased 10 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed pound cake muffins
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, poppy seed, salt and baking soda.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then beat in yogurt and vanilla until well blended. Stir in the flour mixture until moistened thoroughly.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Mixture will be very thick.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving. Makes 24 muffins.

title: creamy vegetable medley(6 servings)
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar, oil, onion and poppy seed together.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: deer roast and gravy("a la microwave")
directions: Place roast in cooking bag.
Pour mushroom soup, onion soup mix, sour cream, water and brown sugar over roast.
Seal bag by tying a knot.
Poke 1 hole in top of bag with toothpick.
Place bag on microwavable plate.
Cook on Medium setting for 10 minutes. After cooking, allow to set for 5 minutes before opening bag. Open bag.
Reserve gravy in bag to pour over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: chicken-veg-all casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; remove from bone.
Tear apart, dice or chop and mix with Veg-All and cream of chicken soup.
Add enough chicken broth to make mixture into gravy thickness.
Put into casserole dish; top with grated cheese.
Top with saltines; pour melted margarine on top.
Cook in a 350° oven until crackers are a golden brown.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen raspberries and juice.
Pour into 5 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
Whip together remaining ingredients until stiff.
Spread over gelatin. Serves 6.

title: holiday eggnog torte
directions: In a small bowl, soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Place bowl in a small pan of hot water to dissolve gelatin completely and keep it warm.

title: rachel's chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken or turkey pieces.
Make gravy from chicken broth, soup and eggs.
Put into large, deep casserole dish.
Cover with crust made of flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over top of meat and soup mixture.
You can add vegetables, if desired.
Bake until crust is brown and done, about one hour. Makes large amount.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, using a mixer. Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot sauce
directions: Wash cilantro, drain well. Hold cilantro over blender and clip off the leafy tips only, trying not to get any stems. Discard the stems. Slice the washed jalapenos into the blender. Pour 1 can of whole tomatoes juice and all into the blender, the pour a little juice from the remaining can into blender. Blend a few seconds until well blended (the juice is needed to get the leafy stuff blended). Pour this into at least a 2 quart container. Pour the remaining can of tomatoes and juice into the blender. Add garlic powder, cumin powder and salt. Blend just a few seconds until blended. Pour into the first batch and stir until mixed well. Serve with chips or whatever you like.

title: beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook meat with diced onion until thoroughly cooked (frying pan on stove).
Drain.
Add 1/4 can enchilada sauce to meat and simmer 5 minutes.
Take off stove and place in bowl.
Heat refried beans in microwave until hot.
Grate cheddar cheese.
Heat tortillas according to package directions (on stove in frying pan with 1 teaspoon oil).
Fill tortillas with meat mixture, a teaspoon or so of refried beans and cheese. roll and place in 13 x 9 pan.
Usually 8 to 12 per pan.
Cover tortillas lengthwise with remaining sauce and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream & salsa.

title: crispy baked spud halves
directions: Scrub and dry baking potatoes. Cut in half lengthwise. Brush cut surface with a mixture of lemon and butter, then dip in a mixture of 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, basil or thyme and a little pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until tender and browned.

title: caramel pie
directions: Fill a large saucepan with water.
Drop entire can of Eagle Brand milk into water when it begins to boil.
Boil 2 hours, never letting the water level fall below the top of the can.
Let cool for 1 hour, then pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: twix cookie
directions: Boil the brown sugar, white sugar, milk and graham cracker crumbs together for 1 to 2 minutes.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and put a layer of whole Club crackers in pan, then pour sugar mixture over crackers, then add another layer of crackers.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips and pour over the second layer of crackers.
Refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except crust.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill at least 2 hours. Top with whipped cream.

title: hoisin hens
directions: Place a heavy wok or pan over high heat.
Add oil.
When hot, add the game hens, breast down.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook 6 minutes, turning at half time.
Add remaining ingredients. Combine well.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 40 minutes, turning at half time.
Remove hens and halve them.
Sauce should be thick and syrupy.
If not, cook, uncovered, for few minutes to reduce.

title: up north chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and place in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello thoroughly until jello mix is no longer grainy.
Drain canned fruits and add to the mixture.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip and chill for 3 to 4 hours until set.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix wet and dry ingredients separately.
Then beat altogether; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°F for 40 - 60 min. or until the whole pie shakes evenly when gently shaken. There should be no thin ripples in the center.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves and trim base of medium head of cauliflower. Wash; precook whole in boiling water 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain. Break into flowerets; place in ungreased shallow baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, mustard and Cheddar cheese and put on top of cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Sprinkle half the cookie crumbs in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cream butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until fluffy.
Prepare pudding mix with milk and vanilla in bowl according to package directions.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.

title: scalloped oysters corn
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle on top 2 tablespoons melted margarine and 1/2 cup crackers (11).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Drain before serving.
Serve with blue/yellow chips (or use as garnish for grilled chicken).

title: pumpkin-pear cake
directions: In bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and cornstarch.
Drain pears, reserving 3 tablespoons of the syrup.
Stir reserved syrup into brown sugar mixture.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange pear halves, small ends to the center and rounded side down, on top of syrup in pan.
In bowl, combine flour, spice, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
In a bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Blend in pumpkin and oil.
Fold flour mixture into pumpkin mixture just until moistened.
Carefully spoon over pears.
Spread mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Loosen from sides of pan.
Invert onto serving plate. Serve warm.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Combine sugar and butter to cream.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly. Stir in flour.
Add flavoring.
Refrigerate.
Roll out on floured wax paper very thin.
Cut with cookie cutter; bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely, as they burn easily.
(Can be dropped from spoonfuls without refrigerating.)
Cookies are best when wrapped in "flour sack" (cotton cloth) and allowed to mellow for several days.

title: joe's wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon, drain on paper towel.
Add onions and salt to oil in skillet.
Heat until tender.
Add sugar, vinegar, eggs and chopped bacon.
Mix with lettuce.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cut sausages into 2-inch pieces.
Place sliced potatoes in large frying pan.
Add a layer of onion slices and a layer of cabbage.
Add butter, salt and pepper to boiling water.
Stir to melt butter and pour over vegetables.
Place sausage pieces on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 25 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Boil 1 minute hard the vinegar and sugar.
Pour this mixture over the onion and cucumbers.
Chill well before serving.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: To meat and onions, add taco seasoning, dressing mix, stewed tomatoes, beans and hominy.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with shredded cheeses on top, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Let Tater Tots thaw.
Mash potatoes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour total (1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered).

title: quick butterscotch pie
directions: Caramelize 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Moisten the cornstarch with a little cold water.
Mix into 1 1/2 cups of water and the beaten egg yolks and salt.
Pour into pie shell and bake.
Cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in vanilla and molasses.
Let cool.
When cool, add beaten egg to molasses mixture.
Sift flour, 1 cup sugar, soda and spices.
Fold molasses mixture into sifted dry ingredients just until mixed.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Roll about 2 tablespoons dough into round ball and coat with remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake no more than 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool on cookie sheet 5 minutes, then transfer to cooling racks.

title: country style biscuits
directions: Makes 15 large biscuits.
Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: easy biscuit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter one 8 x 8-inch pan; set aside. Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Put fruit in bottom of pan and pour dough mix over the fruit.
Do not stir.
Place in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until edges turn brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: beet pickle cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Make a well and add melted butter and vanilla; mix.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in beets, which have been put through a food grinder.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Frost with butter icing.
Distinctively different.
Serves 16.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift salt, baking powder and flour together.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Bake in a large pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, Crisco and white sugar.
Add eggs and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add flour, vanilla, salt, soda and baking powder.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.
Add coconut or nuts, if desired.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon. Combine all ingredients with cream cheese; blend well. Shape in ball or log; put on paper.
Wrap and chill for several hours. Combine nuts and parsley; roll salmon ball in this. May be frozen for future use.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Mix and heat all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into shape using any container lined with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and decorate.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar and let it stand overnight.
Next morning, add eggs, honey and salt.
Whip it with wire whisk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
When it starts "blurping" remove from the heat.
Let it get cold.
Keep covered so doesn't form a crust.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise (not salad dressing).
Pour into jars and refrigerate.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook sausage and onion.
Drain fat. Stir in tomatoes, beans and broth.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until the zucchini is tender.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: apple crunch
directions: Beat whole egg with rotary beater until light.
Gradually add sugar and beat smooth.
Add sifted flour and baking powder, then apples, nuts and vanilla.
Put in lightly greased pan and bake at 275° for 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cottage Pudding Sauce.

title: corn cheddar chowder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In buttered pan, roast onion and yam for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt butter in a 3-quart pan and cook celery, peppers and garlic until tender.
Stir flour into celery mixture until blended.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Stir in onion-yam mixture, corn, turkey, red pepper and spices.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the cheese and continue stirring until cheese is melted.
Garnish with rest of cheese and scallions.

title: 15 minute best fried rice
directions: In large frying pan, brown ground beef on high heat for 5 minutes. Then drain. Bring salt and water to a boil in separate pot. Add rice. Stir and cover. Remove from heat for 5

minutes. Add peas, ketchup, onion, hot sauce and a pinch of salt to ground beef in frying pan and heat on low setting for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, then covering. Add rice and stir thoroughly and serve hot. Makes 4 ample servings.

title: north indian pilaf
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy, nonstick pan.
Add cumin and fennel seed.
When darkened, add cinnamon and cardamon for one minute. Still stirring, add onion, ginger and garlic, cook until onion is soft.
Add vegetables and salt, continue to saute for 5 minutes. Add rice and stir for 2 minutes.
Add boiling water, stir, cover and reduce heat to simmer until water is absorbed (about 40 minutes).
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: monterey artichoke bake
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving 1 tablespoon marinade in a saucepan.
Add onion and garlic to marinade sauce.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8-inch baking pan.
Finely chop artichoke hearts; set aside.

title: barbecue chicken, thai style
directions: Clean chicken; wash and pat dry.
Combine seasonings in blender or food processor and make a coarse paste.
Place paste in a large mixing bowl; add fish soy sauce and mix thoroughly.
Add chicken and mix well with hands.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 hours at room temperature.
Arrange chicken pieces on a barbecue grill or in a broiler; brush evenly with coconut milk.
Cook until done and serve.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In skillet, cook ground beef and drain fat. In separate bowl, mix beef, taco seasoning mix, cheese and water. Unroll crescent rolls. Separate into triangles. Arrange triangles in a circle on a pizza pan with wide ends overlapping in center and points toward the outside. There should be a 5-inch diameter opening in the center. Scoop meat mixture evenly onto the widest end of each triangle. Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of ring. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. After the ring is cooked, place the chopped lettuce, tomato, black olives, onions and cheese in the middle of the ring. To serve, cut in slices.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add evaporated milk, sugar, milk, bananas, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into freezer and freeze according to directions with electric or hand-cranked type freezer.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix butter, cheese, garlic salt and salt well.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in greased oblong Pyrex baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Mix bread cheese and 2 Tbsp. melted butter.
Spread half in greased 1 qt. casserole dish.
Put vegetables on top of breading mixture.
Combine remaining melted butter and onions; cook until onions are tender then blend flour, salt, pepper and milk for gravy.
Add hamburger to gravy.
Pour gravy mixture over vegetable and bread in dish.
Cover with a layer of tomato slices.
Top with remaining bread mixture.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix beans and salsa.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer with sour cream, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: quick and easy dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 10 rolls.
Have your butter ready.
These are wonderful!!!

title: "post pentecost potatoes"
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a greased 2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar in cold water; dissolve well.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir together and add all of the ingredients except ginger ale.
When ready to serve punch, add ginger ale. This punch is good to use with lemon, cherry or strawberry Jell-O.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add flour to thicken. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, sauce, salt and pepper.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in ungreased casserole.
Cover with cooked rice. Pour broth over the rice and chicken to cover about 2/3 the mixture.
Layer the cheese on top.
Put in preheated 350° oven and cook for about 45 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs and baking chocolate.
Gradually beat in flour.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: hobo meal
directions: Crumble hamburger onto tinfoil.
Add remaining ingredients. Fold tinfoil tightly and flatten.
Place on grill or hot coals for approximately 20 minutes.
Flip and grill another 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and ketchup to taste.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour in a large baking dish.
Top with the crackers and melted margarine. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick picante dip(simple, but surprisingly good!)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and chill.
Garnish with cilantro sprig.
This is the basic recipe.
You can determine the "hot" factor of this dip by choosing mild, medium or hot Picante sauce. Also, the Picante sauce can be replaced with any good restaurant salsa or your own favorite salsa recipe.
If you really want to spice it up, add some fresh jalapeo pepper, chopped very fine.

title: top round with mushrooms
directions: Place steaks in shallow baking dish.
Combine oil, onion, vinegar, salt and oregano.
Pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate several hours, turning meat occasionally.
Melt a little butter or margarine in a skillet.
Add mushrooms and saute.
Remove steak from marinade.
Place on broiler pan and cook about 4 minutes per side, basting with marinade.

title: navy sos recipe
directions: Cook beef with onions in own fat until beef loses its color. Drain off excess fat. Add tomatoes, mace or nutmeg, salt and pepper. Stir well. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Enjoy!

title: pizza burgers
directions: *May substitute 15 ounce jar of Ragu.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Mix everything else into pudding.

title: karen trump's slush
directions: Combine sugar
and
water.
Bring to boil for 1 minute. Refrigerate
until
cold.
Add
pineapple
juice, orange juice concentrate,
lemonade
concentrate
and bananas to cold sugar and water and freeze.
Put frozen concentrate mixture in glass and add 7-Up and rum to taste.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake in 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ann's crab cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion and lemon juice and form in shape of a ball.
Put in a sealed container and place in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Ten minutes before serving, spread dip (ball) on silver platter.
Spread 1/2 bottle chili sauce on top of dip mixture.
Layer fresh crab meat on chili sauce (you may use imitation crab).
Sprinkle with fresh chopped parsley.
Serve this dip with Triscuits crackers.

title: arizona salad with dressing
directions: Tear leaf lettuce.
Cut cabbage into strips and chop on diagonal.
Put in large bowl.
Chop green onions and add to lettuce mix.
Crumble Ramen noodles and add to mix.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Saute almonds and sesame seeds in oil; drain and add to lettuce just before serving.

title: salt pork cake
directions: Pour boiling water over pork; let stand until cool.
Dissolve baking soda in molasses.
Add to water and salt pork.
Add sugar, raisins and spices.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Pour into 10-inch greased square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble cookies to cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk; set aside to thicken.
Mix cream cheese with 3/4 cup milk and Cool Whip, then add to pudding mixture. Pour over cookies, then use crushed cookies for top as garnish.

title: chef salad dressing
directions: Shake up and refrigerate.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Start heating oven to 450°.
Generously grease a 9-inch square pan; heat in oven while mixing batter.
In bowl, stir together baking soda, corn meal and salt.
Add egg mixture all at once. Beat until smooth.
Pour in heated pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick pear sundaes
directions: Place a scoop of ice cream in each pear cavity; top with caramel sauce.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: veal paprika with poppy seed and noodles
directions: Cut steak into 4 portions and roll in the seasoned flour.
In heavy skillet, heat some oil and brown meat on both sides.
Add water and cover; simmer on low heat until tender, adding a little more water if necessary to prevent sticking.

title: fat-free cheese dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the Ro-Tel in blender until smooth. Serve with vegetables or low-fat chips.
Add additional Ro-Tel if desired for a spicier taste.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix pork, onion, salt, pepper and rice.
Plunge cabbage leaves into boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Put a portion of meat mixture on each leaf.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots together in salted water to cover until tender; drain well.
Drain pimentos; chop.
Add soup, sour cream and pimentos to squash mixture; mix well.
Mix butter and stuffing mix.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in 2 greased casseroles.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Yields 24 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, beat together the peanut butter, brown sugar, egg and baking soda until smooth and well blended. Stir in chips. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, spacing mounds about 2-inches apart. Bake one baking sheet at a time until the cookies are puffed and slightly golden but still soft to the touch, about 10 minutes. Cool about 5 minutes before removing from baking sheet onto wire rack.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in large glass bowl.
Add peas in layer, then cauliflower, then bacon bits.
Sprinkle with dry salad dressing mix.
Cover with mayonnaise (may be thinned with small amount milk) as though icing a cake.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
May be made a day ahead. Toss to mix all ingredients immediately prior to serving.

title: plain squash
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain well.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on low heat until onion is tender.

title: velvet supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; spread in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: old fashioned corn chowder
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil (and a little water as needed to prevent sticking) for about 10 minutes.
Stir frequently to prevent browning.
Add carrots and potato (again adding a little water as needed) and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent browning.
Add flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add rice milk, water and vegetable bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook at medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add frozen corn and cook for another 10 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Remove from heat.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Puree half the soup in a blender.
Return blended soup back to the pot.
Add pepper to taste.
(The blended soup gives the chowder nice body, but be sure to leave half of it chunky.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk together. Then add Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: "aunt mary's" pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, Crisco, vanilla and lemon together until creamy.
Add eggs gradually.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Add alternately with 1 cup milk.
Batter will be heavy.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan approximately 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hot sour soup
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil; add pork.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Skim off foam and add thinly sliced mushrooms and bamboo shoots, shrimp, soy sauce, salt and sherry. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add vinegar, pepper and bean cake (tofu).
Cook 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture to soup, stirring gently, for 1 minute.
Continue stirring, while slowly adding eggs, in threads. Stir in sesame oil and sprinkle with green onions.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in lard until it resembles corn meal.
Beat egg, vinegar and water together.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend thoroughly, using a pastry blender.
Let rest. Roll out to desired size.
Will make 2 full pie crusts.

title: egg nog
directions: You will also need 1 glass.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Place bread in prepared baking dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Combine evaporated milk, eggs, dry mustard, onion powder in medium bowl.
Pour evenly over bread and cheese.
Sprinkle with sausage, cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in flour.
Cover and chill 3 hours.

title: salad d'amour
directions: Pat dry everything with paper towel, except chow mein noodles. Make the sauce.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Dissolve over hot water.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Beat in sugar and vanilla. Add cooled gelatin and beat until it forms peaks.
Spread over cake.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over row of wings in 9 x 13-inch pan (18 per pan).
Bake 4 to 5 hours in 250° oven.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add yeast to first mixture and then add beaten eggs.
Stir in 4 cups flour and beat thoroughly.
Stir in 4 more cups of flour.
Do not knead!!
May be kept for several days in the refrigerator if it is tightly covered.
When ready to use, shape into rolls; stand in warm place until doubled in bulk.

title: pork chop casserole #2
directions: Salt and pepper and flour pork chops.
Brown in skillet. Remove chops and pour out grease, then cut up other ingredients in quarters and place in large skillet.
Put chops over vegetables. Salt and pepper all; cover with water.
Shake Worcestershire sauce over chops.
Put 2 to 3 bay leaves over all.
Cover and cook until done on top of stove.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix broth and soup.
Add spaghetti, eggs, cheese and mushrooms.
Fold in chicken and broccoli.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Top with crumbs coated with margarine.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mrs. patterson's tomato sauce
directions: Use
a
to 8 quart pot.
Start cooking on high for 30 minutes,
stirring
occasionally.
Then
on
low
heat
for
45 minutes
to
1 hour, stirring often.
During last 15 minutes of cooking,
add 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour to thicken. After cooking, remove bag of pickling spice.
Put in clean jars and seal at once.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 cake mix into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels and milk in a pan over low heat.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture over top of cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour remaining cake batter over mixture and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Needs no icing.

title: no-knead bowl bread
directions: Choose a 7 qt. plastic bowl that has a lid which will seal tightly. Place the warm water into the bowl. Dissolve yeast in the water with 1/4 c. sugar. Let stand 5 minutes while preparing the remaining ingredients. Add the flour, remaining sugar, oil, salt, and eggs; stir until well blended. Cover the container with the lid and seal. Allow to stand at room temperature about 1 hour until the lid pops. Divide the dough into 3 parts and place into 3 (9 X 5) loaf pans that have been rubbed with oil. Let dough rise again in a warm place another 30 minutes or until the loaves sound hollow when tapped.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Can be mixed ahead and/or stored in refrigerator a couple of days.
This is great with vegetables.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain and cool.
Cut peppers, tomatoes and onions into bite-size pieces.
Add to noodles and pour Wish-Bone over.
Mix and serve.
Makes a lot.
You can cut it down.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into potatoes.
Heat 1 1/2 inches oil in frypan.
Fry to golden brown.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Combine lemonade and orange juice concentrates with sugar and water. Add partially frozen strawberries, pineapple and juice, bananas and cherries. Spoon into pretty serving dishes and freeze. When ready to serve, remove from freezer 1/2 to 1 hour before serving until this becomes slushy.

title: chocolate and butterscotch rice krispie squares
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and 1 cup peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add 8 cups Rice Krispies and "stir well."
Pour 1/2 mixture in greased pan; chill.
Combine chocolate bits, 2 tablespoons water and 4 tablespoons margarine over hot water.
Add confectioners sugar (sifted).
Stir.
Spread over first chilled mixture.
Add balance of butterscotch mixture.
Pat down firm.
Cut when cool, but not cold.

title: turkey divan(microwavable)
directions: Blend the first seven ingredients into a sauce.
Cook 4 minutes in microwave at 70% power, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Cook broccoli, place on ovenproof platter.
Pour 1/2 of the sauce over broccoli.
Arrange turkey over broccoli, add Parmesan cheese to the remainder of the sauce, pour it over the turkey and sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Broil in oven until sauce bubbles and is lightly browned (or microwave at 70% power for 6 to 7 minutes).

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, peanut butter and oleo together.
Add eggs, bananas and buttermilk and beat.
Add salt, soda, baking powder, vanilla and flour.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Also can be made in tea biscuit pans (we call them Banana Bites; they are great in lunches).
Bake in tea biscuit pans for 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen banana bites.

title: grandma's home made wine(from grandmother dora thalmann clasen)
directions: Pour fruit juice into 5-gallon stone crock.
Add water and sugar (warm water works faster).
Let sit until done working; pour into jugs.
Makes about 3 1/2 gallons.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together in double boiler.
Roll 1 cup graham crackers into chopped nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and press in glass pan and place in icebox.

title: seafood appetizers
directions: *Two and one-half pounds all shrimp can be used in lieu of part tuna and scallops.

title: schinkenfleckel(ham and noodle casserole)
directions: In
a large mixing bowl, combine cooked noodles, ground ham, cottage
cheese, sour cream, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt
and pepper.
Stir gently until well mixed.
Spoon noodle mixture into
a
lightly
greased
2-quart
casserole
dish. Sprinkle Parmesan
cheese
on
top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven
for
20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rich hot rolls
directions: Scald milk, add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water, stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture; beat well by hand or electric mixer at low speed for 1 minute.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour a little at a time, to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth, satiny and no longer sticky (5 to 8 minutes). Place in lightly greased bowl.
Invert to grease top; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Divide in 1/2 and shape as desired.
Brush tops lightly with melted butter.
Let rise until double, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 30 rolls.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Dip in melted butter and roll in crumbs and herb mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: 5-hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours or in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator overnight. Stir well after removing from refrigerator. Fill muffin tin 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: canning fresh salmon
directions: After salmon is cleaned and ready to cook, cut in chunks and pack in jars, leaving about an inch at top.
Put 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vinegar and 2 tablespoons ketchup to each quart. (Don't cover with water; it makes own juice.)
Put lids on and cook 3 hours to cold pack or 90 minutes after control jiggles with 10 pounds pressure.
Same for quarts or pints.

title: brown bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, molasses and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and mix until moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Grease 2 (4 x 8-inch) bread pans.
Pour mixture into both pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion until tender; drain off fat.
Add evaporated milk, green chillies, enchilada sauce and soups; mix well.

title: garden combo
directions: Heat zucchini and butter in skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are hot, about 5 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)

title: worlds best cookies
directions: Drop-size of walnut flatten with fork on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: confetti rice
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels; drain all but 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add rice, carrots, celery and peas; cook until heated through, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in bacon.

title: georgia peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese with mixer until blended.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with crushed nuts; cover and chill.

title: dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Combine in bowl with sugar, onion, oleo, dill, soda, egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour to form stiff dough.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch dough down and put in well-greased loaf pan.
Let rise.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown around 40 to 50 minutes.
Optional:
Brush with oleo and sprinkle with salt.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese crackers
directions: In food processor, combine cheese and butter.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add to processor; process until just combined.
Remove and form into 2 long, skinny rolls.
Chill (up to several days).
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Makes 60.

title: ann's ham loaf
directions: Have butcher cut off all fat on pork and grind both together. Mix pork with onion, bell pepper, egg, bread and milk.
Shape in loaf and place in loaf pan or casserole.
Cover generously with brown sugar and bottle of chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with whipping cream and mustard to taste.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put layers of tortillas, onions, meat and cheese in baking dish.
Repeat.
Cover with soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Bake, covered, to prevent drying out.

title: banana delight
directions: Combine butter, flour, pecans and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned, then cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Mix well and put over cooled crust.
Slice bananas on top of this.
Mix 3 cups milk with pudding.
Pour over bananas; refrigerate until firm.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: patti jacuzzi's potato salad
directions: Cube and boil potatoes in salted water until done.
Drain. Add chopped eggs, onion, cottage cheese, salt, mustard, Durkee, mayonnaise and celery seed.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Even better the next day.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Pierce roasts in several places; season lightly with salt and lemon pepper and tenderizer.
Place roasts in large plastic bag set in a deep bowl.

title: bran banana muffins
directions: In a large bowl, add first 7 ingredients.
Mix well and make a large hole in the center.
Set aside.
Combine egg and brown sugar
in
a
medium
bowl;
beat at medium speed of an electric mixer
until smooth.
Stir in bananas, nuts, oil and vanilla; beat
well.
Add
to
flour mixture; stir just until dry ingredients
are
moistened.
Spoon
batter
into greased muffin pans,
filling
full.
Bake
at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove immediately.
Let cool on wire racks.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars until light. Beat egg and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: holiday squash with cranberries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat squash with 3 tablespoons melted butter and the eggs.
Slowly stir in cranberries, sugar, salt and pepper; spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Drizzle on remaining butter; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake, uncovered, for approximately 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer all items in order listed.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; gradually add chocolate and vanilla. Add one egg at a time and beat for 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 3 or 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream and toasted, slivered almonds.

title: date cake
directions: Cover dates with boiling water, cool to lukewarm.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Add date mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 8-inch square pan in a moderate oven 35 to 40 minutes (loaf pan can be used).

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs and beat well. Blend in remaining ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan. Mix together a little sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of bread before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black bean soup
directions: Heat oil in large pot. Saute onions, garlic and thyme about 8 minutes. Onion should be golden. Add beans, 1 cup bean liquid reserved and the rest of the ingredients. Bring soup to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until flavors blend and soup thickens slightly. Stir occasionally. This should take about 20 minutes. Working in batches, puree soup in blender until smooth. Put puree back into pot. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add a spoonful of sour cream or plain yoghurt when serving. This soup can be frozen.

title: soft center cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place butter in 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish and heat in oven to melt.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in 1 cup milk and beaten eggs, then stir in buttermilk and pour into hot Pyrex dish.
Now follow carefully, pour 1 cup milk over cornmeal mixture, do not stir; bake 35 minutes.
This is a cornbread with a custard layer.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, cook rhubarb for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan over low heat. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut, then chocolate chips evenly.
Pour condensed milk evenly over layers.
Top with nuts.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: weight watcher one point muffins
directions: Mix together and spoon in 12 count muffin pan (regular size). Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler or use microwave oven. If using microwave, follow directions for melting chocolate, being careful not to burn.
Wash and dry strawberries before dipping in melted chocolate.
Leave hulls on strawberries to use as handle and to "decorate" dipped berries.
Dip each berry, leaving a little of red showing.
Easy, elegant and delicious.
May use white chocolate for half the berries.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Arrange bread cubes in baking dish.
Cover with cubed cheese. Beat eggs until foamy; add milk.
Also add salt.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese.
Spread flat and smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° about one hour.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare
broccoli
according
to directions on package. Drain and
set
aside.
Prepare
two
cups
rice according to directions on
box.
Drain and set aside.
Cut cheese in small cubes;
set aside.
Mix
all
ingredients together.
Stir and microwave from 2 to 5 minutes on High (timing will depend upon the size of the oven).
Stir and let stand for 5 minutes prior to serving.

title: uncle mac's coconut custard
directions: Melt margarine; beat eggs and add other ingredients, leaving coconut until last.
Stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, flour, oil and eggs. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: heart attack lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, adding grated onion. Drain beef of fat.
Add sauce along with basil, garlic and pepper. Simmer and stir.
Add olive oil to a pot of boiling water.

Add lasagna noodles and boil until limp; drain and separate strips. Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread thin layer of sauce, then layer cottage or Ricotta cheese, layer of Mozzarella, layer of Cheddar and layer of pasta; repeat.
Crisscross lasagna noodles while layering.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add a top layer of sour cream.
Return to oven just long enough to warm the sour cream layer, approximately 5 minutes.
Let stand; cut to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix and roll out small balls or flatten and drop in chocolate until coated.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain and set aside. Cook and stir onion and garlic in dressing in skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Mash potatoes over low heat. Stir in onion mixture, cheese and milk. Add seasonings. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Top with crumbs and oleo. Bake 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pour over beets and boil for 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal at once.
If beets are large, cut in halves or fourths.

title: lamb noodle stroganoff
directions: Cook lamb with garlic until browned; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with meat mixture.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth; stir in onions.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.

title: baked fudge
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat the eggs; add to the flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan over water (pan doesn't touch bottom) in a 300° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, oleo and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Beat into first mixture. Add remaining ingredients and knead into first mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.

title: no fail kim-chee
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve 1/2 cup salt in 1 gallon of water; mix well. Add cut up cabbage (1-inch length). Soak in salted water; sprinkle rest of the salt on top. Let it wilt about 2 hours, turning occasionally. Wash; drain well.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, baking powder and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs.
Stir into eggs in this order:
sugar, honey, peanut butter, milk and dry ingredients.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Into a cup, spoon 1 rounded tablespoon butter.
Press the back of a spoon into each filled cup to make a well.
Spoon into each well 1 teaspoon of jelly.
Cover jelly by evenly dividing remaining batter into the cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with extra peanut butter and jelly on the side.
Makes 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and put 1/2 of dressing mix in bottom.
Put cooked chicken on top of this.
In a saucepan mix together milk, soups and broth; heat until warm and well mixed.
Pour soup mixture over cooked chicken.
Put remaining dressing on top and bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use as a dip for any fruit.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Beat again.
Add flour and soda gradually, and continue beating.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Mix ingredients together with potatoes.
Put into greased casserole.
Put bacon and tomatoes on top as garnish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: minestrone(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook garlic, onion and celery in Wesson oil in large kettle. Stir in Hunt's tomato paste and next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook for 15 minutes more.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, butter, salt, sugar, baking powder and egg to a crumble. Pare and slice apples to 1 1/2-inch depth in 8 x 12-inch pan. Cover with crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown. Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: potato wedges
directions: Shake mixture in bag with potatoes.
Brush margarine on potatoes. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and Cool Whip together, then add crushed pineapple. Drain fruit cocktail and add to mixture.

title: kentucky fried chicken cole slaw
directions: Mix and let sit 2 hours.

title: pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir fruit into pancake mix, milk, egg and cinnamon.
Pour into a greased pan and bake for 10 minutes.

title: apple betty
directions: Peel and
cut apples into eights.
Place in large bowl. Add sugar,
brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and toss lightly. Place in
greased
9-inch
pan and set aside.
Combine and mix well the flour, oats, brown sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add butter and cut
in
with
pastry
blender
or fork.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies; put 3/4 of them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together the oleo and cheese.
Mix in powdered sugar and Cool Whip; set aside.
Mix up pudding with 3 cups milk instead of 4. Mix this with first mixture.
Pour over cookie crumbs, then put the rest of crumbs on top.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; beat in Cool Whip and line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding mix over graham crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers; pour remaining pudding mix over grahams and top with more grahams. Heat 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup milk.
Heat to boiling and boil 1 minute.
Add 1/3 cup cocoa and 1 stick margarine; heat until margarine is melted and icing is smooth.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over cake.
Chill several hours.

title: harry's slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Mix milk and butter together.
Chop Velveeta; add to milk and butter mixture and melt until smooth.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Bake until lightly brown (approximately 20 minutes).

title: broccoli dressings
directions: Mix and pour over broccoli, chopped.

title: ham chowder
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart pot over medium heat. Cut potatoes into chunks. Add to margarine along with onion, carrots and celery. Cook 10 to 12 minutes, stirring until carrots are not quite done. Whisk 1/2 cup milk with flour until smooth.

Stir into vegetable mixture along with ham and remaining milk. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Add corn, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes more until thick and vegetables are tender.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix broth, soup, milk and onion.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer tortillas, chilies, chicken, cheese and broth mixture until all is used, ending with cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake about 1 hour at 300° without cover.
Serve and enjoy.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and use two teaspoons for each cup of tea.

title: spinach bread
directions: Roll out dough.
Spread ingredients.
Roll up as jelly roll. Pinch ends.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Can use sausage.

title: hearty macaroni dish
directions: Heat milk; add cheese, chopped onion, green pepper, butter and salt.
Mix with beaten egg yolks.
Blend in macaroni and bread crumbs all in a casserole dish.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a pan of water for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and salt together.
Add a little at a time to cream mixture, blending in.
Then blend in carrots and nuts.
Makes 4 or 5 layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven baked fried chicken
directions: Crush corn flakes.
Roll chicken breasts in corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: granola bars
directions: Melt honey and peanut butter.
Add raisins and oatmeal.
Stir together.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet or shallow dish and cool.
Cut into bars.

title: pinwheel cake and cream(a quick and easy dessert to make with any fruit!)
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, orange rind and peaches.
Arrange pound cake slices on serving plate.
Spoon pudding mixture evenly over center of cake slices.
Arrange fruit in pudding mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all but the last 2 ingredients and pour into dish with margarine, but do not stir.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to peaches.
Pour peaches into crust mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Never stir ingredients.

title: fruit christmas cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in extract.
Add flour.
Mix well. Shape level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Roll in nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Indent centers.
Fill with preserves. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sourdough bread #1
directions: Sprinkle yeast and sugar over water in large bowl; stir to dissolve.
Let stand until foamy, about 5 minutes.
Add flour and whisk until smooth.
Cover and let stand in warm place until sour aroma develops, stirring daily, 2 to 3 days.
Put in 1 cup covered crocks or jars and refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups.
Now go to Sourdough Bread #2.

title: dill mustard
directions: A double boiler which has a lid is required, either stainless steel or glass. Mix together first six ingredients, cover and let sit for 4 - 6 hours. After sitting for the time period, place double boiler on stove. Beat two eggs and add to mixture. Cook 8 - 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour into jars, cover and refrigerate.

title: best ever salad
directions: Cut pared tomatoes and peppers into bite-sized pieces.
Grate onion over top.
Sprinkle with salt; cover and let stand 15 minutes or longer.
Sprinkle with oil; toss and serve.

title: cal's chili
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Pour off excess fat; add rest of ingredients, then add water.
Mix well.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: crock-pot barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan with lemon juice for 30 minutes. Drain; place in crock-pot and cover with onion.
Pour on barbecue sauce and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 5 hours.

title: crab meat sandwiches
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a double boiler until melts, then add crab meat and onion.
Place mixture on hamburger buns and place under broiler.
Watch closely as cheese browns fast.

title: vegetable pitas
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a bowl.
Toss gently; combine parsley flakes and next 6 ingredients, stir well.
Add to vegetable mixture, tossing well.
Spoon 1 cup vegetable mixture into each 5 pita halves, reserving remaining pita half for another use.
Sprinkle with cheese; cut each pita half in half.
Makes 5 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Combine sugar and pineapple in saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir until syrupy.
When cake is done, turn out on serving dish or leave in pan.
Poke holes in top of cake.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Beat cream cheese with milk; sprinkle pudding in, a little at a time. When mixed, use to ice cake.
Top with bananas.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Decorate with cherries. (Refrigerate.)

title: quick peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter with Cool Whip.
Stir together well.
Pour into pie crust.
Let chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Add green pepper and onions.
Cook on High 3 to 5 minutes, until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Stir and drain fat.
Then add seasoning, tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives, water and chili powder.
Cook on Low 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened.
Blend sour cream, eggs and pepper together in a small bowl.
Place 2 tortillas on bottom of a 12 x 18-inch dish.
Top with half the meat mixture, followed by half the sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle corn chips and cheese on top.
Cook on Low 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese melts.
Rotate dish halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
