title: autumn soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook and salt onions with meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes; cover and simmer for 10 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple with lemon juice, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool. Add apricot baby food and mix well.
Fold in fruit, including cherries (red and green cherries could be used for Christmas).

title: easy yeast hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add shortening, salt and sugar. Alternate, adding milk and flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Make rolls and place on greased cake pan.
Let rise and bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: frosty pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, pumpkin, milk and spices in a mixing bowl.
Mix slowly with electric mixer or by hand until just blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon mixture into pie crust.
Freeze until firm for 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt the butterscotch bits and chocolate chips together in top of double boiler.
Fold in the noodles and nuts or coconut, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Allow time for candy to set before storing in airtight container.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Spray an unheated large skillet with cooking spray.
Preheat over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook about 6 minutes or until lightly browned, turning to brown evenly.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, pepper, mushrooms, onion, water, and seasonings.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Remove chicken from skillet; cover chicken and keep warm.
Simmer tomato mixture, uncovered, about 5 minutes or to desired consistency.

title: black velvet chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add spices.
Cook low 2 hours on top of stove. This is medium-hot.
Season to taste.

title: devil's food cake(quick-mix)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/3 cup milk, unbeaten eggs and melted chocolate.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 round, greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half of onion.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer. Sprinkle cheese on and bake for the last 5 minutes.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: Shape first six ingredients into meatballs.
Fry and drain. Add cooked meatballs to chicken broth along with spinach.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add cooked tortellini.

title: chocolate lover's cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions of box using two 8 or 9-inch round pans. Prepare Jell-O pudding mix according to directions on box and let sit until firm. Layer cake on bottom; top with pudding. Repeat with 2nd cake and top with pudding.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle Heath bits over Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 triangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with reserved 1 tablespoon butter.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: To prepare pumpkin:
Peel and deseed pumpkin; cut into pieces and boil until soft.
Drain.
Mash pumpkin.
Preheat oven to 450°. In mixing bowl, mix all ingredients; stir.
Put mixture into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes (or until firm).

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Crush potato chips or French fried onion rings or chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except shredded Cheddar cheese and cook over low heat.
Top with shredded Cheddar.
Makes 7 cups.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in bottom of greased
9 x 13-inch pan. Put cake mix over the coconut and pecans.

title: theresa's seafood surprise
directions: Put 1 package crushed Ritz crackers in melted butter on bottom of large casserole dish.
Combine crab meat and shrimp and saute in 1 tablespoon margarine (Seafood Magic or liquid crab).
Combine Velveeta cheese, evaporated milk and Tabasco.
Put seafood in casserole over crackers.
Pour cheese mixture over seafood. Sprinkle more Ritz.
Bake at 400° covered until it bubbles on all sides.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
While rice is hot, stir in onion, vinegar, oil, curry powder and salt.
Gently add peas.
Chill.
After rice mixture is completely cool, add celery and mayonnaise.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Toss with chicken mixture. Cover and chill for several hours.
Yields 7 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let all cheese come to room temperature and mix well in small bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Let chill slightly and roll in a ball or in logs and roll in chopped nuts or parsley.
(A little chopped parsley may be added to cheese ball, if desired.)
Serve with crackers, especially good with Triscuits.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature, then beat until fluffy.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk.
Stir until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Chill. Garnish top with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Using most of shortening, fry chicken until golden brown.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of oil for a separate pan.
Slowly cook garlic, onions, pepper and mushrooms in reserved oil until soft.
Pour over chicken.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and oregano.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Stir occasionally while cooking.
Serve with spaghetti noodles.

title: homemade "cracker jack"
directions: Mix together the popped corn and peanuts in a large bowl or a roast pan.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in the brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour over warm popped corn and peanuts mixture while tossing until popped corn and nuts are well coated.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Make sure every piece of popcorn has been moved.
Turn out on aluminum foil.
Store in a tight container.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes, then prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: anise seed cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar;
add
eggs
and
seasonings. Combine with
flour, dry ingredients and nuts.
This is a soft dough.
Drop
enough
onto
a
floured board and roll into a 1 1/2-inch roll the length of your cookie sheet, usually 4 rolls to each
cookie
sheet.
Bake
at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or slightly
golden.
Remove
from
oven and slice 1/2 inch wide. Lay sliced
side
down
on
cookie sheet and return to oven to brown for about 10 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and pie filling.
Top with your favorite dressing or Cool Whip.

title: lemon lush
directions: First layer:
Mix flour, butter, and nuts and press into 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.
(Do not melt butter- leave at room temperature and cut into flour to a crumbly mixture.)

title: chili con queso
directions: On the stove, slowly melt Velveeta.
Add salsa to taste.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: pound cake fix-up
directions: Slice thawed pound cake horizontally in half.
Spread soft cream cheese on bottom layer, then top with preserves.
Replace top layer.
Top with soft-style cream cheese and melted preserves.

title: fruit punch with sherbet
directions: In large punch bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Chill in freezer for about 8 to 12 minutes.
Serve with a spoon and a straw.
Serves 4.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Mix crackers and butter together and put over bean-cheese-soup mixture to form a crust.
Bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes.

title: stuffed pepper
directions: Cook rice half done.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff peppers and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put mini marshmallows on bottom
of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not overlap.
Mix cake according to the directions on the box.
Pour over the marshmallows.
Take thawed strawberries and mix jello (dry) into the strawberries.
Spoon the strawberries over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Your marshmallows will come to the top and berries will go to the bottom.
May place Cool Whip on each piece when serving.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Break eggs into a small bowl.
Beat with a fork until light. Add a few shakes of salt and a tablespoon of milk.
Pour into a greased, hot frying pan.
Cook until slightly moist, scraping up egg every minute or so.

title: brown rice
directions: Fry the bacon in a large skillet. Remove from skillet, drain on paper towel and crumble. Place the onions and the celery in the bacon drippings and saute until tender. Add the mushrooms, rice, and soy sauce. Cover, and cook for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally. Stir in the beaten egg and cook until the egg is done. Add the bacon and mix well. Extra soy sauce may be added.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower for a few minutes until tender. Place in casserole dish.
Mix cheese and cream of chicken soup together and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle French-fried onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mary's better than ever cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, pour in cake mix, add sour cream, oil and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add grated chocolate, mix well and add chocolate chips.
Flour and grease a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour in cake mixture.
Cook about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in margarine until tender. Remove garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend flour and cheese.
Add sugar, oil and milk and stir with a fork.
Scrape dough onto floured wax paper and cut with glass. Bake at 400° until done.
Yields 24 biscuits.

title: turkey rice soup
directions: Marinate turkey in beer and 4 ounces Worcestershire sauce for 4 hours.
Then bake in clay cooker for 3 hours at 300°.
Remove turkey from cooker, debone and dice meat.
Reserve broth for use as soup stock.
Combine all ingredients in covered 6-quart soup pot and cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Simmer to reheat.
Keeps well in refrigerator for one week.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Add milk, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for one hour, until done.

title: western omelet
directions: In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, pour scrambled eggs in. Let cook thoroughly on one side.
Carefully flip omelet over. Place remaining ingredients in the middle of the cooked side of the eggs.
Let cheese melt slightly, then flip omelet mixture in half. Omelet is cooked when eggs are done.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream all together in electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Add small can evaporated milk and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix well and bake about 30 minutes at 350°; top with marshmallows and broil 5 minutes.

title: tostada platter
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain meat.
Add chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Set aside and keep warm.
In a saucepan combine undrained green beans and kidney beans; heat and drain.
In heavy skillet, heat 1/4-inch cooking oil.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil for 20 to 40 seconds on each side or until crisp and golden.
Drain on paper toweling.
Keep warm in foil in 250° oven. Place tortillas in center of dinner plate.
Layer ingredients, tostadas, meat, beans, tomato, lettuce and cheese.
Serve at once. Pass salad dressing.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed well with Pam and coated with sugar instead of flour. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumbers with onions
directions: In a shallow bowl, with a fork, beat together the salt, sugar, vinegar and water.
Mix in cucumbers and onion.
Cover and chill for 30 to 60 minutes.
Serve with a slotted spoon or drain before serving.
Save liquid in which to refrigerate any cucumbers and onion leftover.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Bring water, butter and salt to rolling boil in heavy saucepan.
Add flour all at once and cook over low heat, beating vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and has a satin sheen.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove and cool.

title: "sock it to me" cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the cinnamon and brown sugar.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 mixture into cake pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter and add the rest of the cake mixture to cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes, 325° for glass dish or 350° for heavy aluminum Bundt pan.

title: sesame pita triangles
directions: Separate each pita bread crosswise into rounds, cut each round into 8 wedges. Place wedges cut side down on ungreased baking sheets. Combine soy sauce, oil, water and garlic powder; brush mixture evenly over wedges.
Sprinkle evenly with sesame seed. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight container.
Substitute tortillas for pita bread.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add other ingredients and bring to boil.	Simmer 5 minutes or longer, stirring constantly.
Add more ketchup or water if more sauce is needed.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain.
Add cheese after beef has cooled.
Add tomatoes and lettuce (cut into bite size pieces) and crumbled Doritos.
Mix well with taco sauce and salad dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: black-eyed peas and ham hocks
directions: Cover ham hocks with cold water and cook gently until meat is tender. Remove meat and put aside until cool enough to handle. Discard bones and skin and trim off most of fat.
Do not discard the water in which ham hocks were cooked.
When this water has gotten cold, skim off the fat that has risen to the top.
Now wash the dried peas and remove all the faulty peas.
Put the washed peas into the water in which the ham hocks were cooked and let them soak overnight.
Next day, add ham, chopped onion (optional) and salt. Cover pot and simmer for 1 hour or so until peas are tender.
Add more water and seasonings as needed. While it is not necessary to soak the peas in the water in which the ham hocks were cooked, that water definitely adds to the flavor.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
With mixer beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes.
Slowly beat in salad oil.
Beat in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and extract.
With spoon stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done.
Remove cake from pan.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and water.
Mix well. Stir in apples.
Lightly oil two loaf pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tests done.

title: easy microwave apple cobbler
directions: Crumble six cookies in bottom of shallow microwavable dish. Spread pie filling over cookies.
Crumble 6 remaining cookies on top.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add milk and beat to make a smooth batter like the consistency of pancake batter.
Melt oleo in a dish or pan and add fruit.
Pour batter over fruit and bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° to 425° oven.
Serve hot or cold, plain or without whipped cream or ice cream.

title: grape pie
directions: Make pastry for 2 crust pie.
Mix tapioca, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar together.
Mix in grapes. Fill pie shell. Dot with butter and add water.
Put top pastry crust on.
Flute edges. Cover edges with tinfoil.
Slit top crust in 6 places. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave dumplings
directions: Put broth
in
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes
on
High until boiling.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt
into mixture bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like corn meal.
Add milk until mixture is moistened but not smooth.
Drop
into broth by teaspoonfuls.	Do not cover. Cook 6 minutes on High.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes on High until dumplings are
firm.	This makes a gravy.
For thinner gravy, add more broth.

title: mock crab salad(made with parsnips and pimiento)
directions: Peel parsnips and grind coarsely.
Add celery, onion, chopped pimiento and olives.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add salad dressing.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over mushrooms.
Marinate for a few days in a covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: steak soup
directions: Saute meat and onions.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Simmer several hours on low.
May also be simmered in crock-pot on low for several hours.

title: banana fizz favorite
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to Jell-O; stir until thickened. Remove any unmelted ice.
Put banana slices into glasses.
Measure out 1 1/3 cups Jell-O and spoon over banana slices.
Whip remaining Jell-O with electric mixer until fluffy, thick and about doubled.
Pour over Jell-O in glasses.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over medium direct heat. Add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper, then add chicken broth, cream and milk.
Bring to a boil over direct heat, then put pan over simmering water and cook for 5 minutes.
Add about 1/2 of hot sauce to egg yolks, mix then return sauce with yolks to remaining sauce.
Stir and cook for 1 minute. Add chicken and pimento and cook until heated.
Serve over hot buttered toast points, baking powder biscuits or rice or in patty shells.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Remove bread immediately from pan and onto a cooling rack.
Cool before serving or slicing. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whip ingredients just until blended.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Freeze several hours.
Top with dollop of Cool Whip before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake 3 layers according to box directions.
Mix sugar and sour cream.
Add coconut; mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Frost cake and chill.

title: spaghetti
directions: Dice onion and pepper and fry with beef until brown; stir to keep meat crumbled.
Add other ingredients except spaghetti. Cook, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes in saucepan.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Serve spaghetti with sauce poured on top.

title: meat balls
directions: Roll and shape into balls.
Broil on cookie sheet.
Drain fat and add to sauce.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingreds. together. Chill and serve with apples.
Great for after school snacks

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Cream butter and sugars and beat in eggs.
Add zucchini and pineapple and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: steak parmigiana
directions: Combine flour and cheese.
Dip steak into egg and coat with flour mixture.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in a shallow baking dish. Saute onion in oil.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over steak and top with cheese slices.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy hot wings
directions: Barbecue hot wings on grill.
Season with garlic salt.
Cook until brown on each side; remove.
Add as much hot sauce as you want.
Reheat in microwave oven 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Serve hot.

title: potato chili soup
directions: Dice up potatoes and onion.
Cover with water and cook until done.
Add oleo, salt, pepper and brick chili.
Cook until brick chili and oleo are melted.
Add can of milk; do not boil after you add milk.
Serves about 6.

title: black bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan or stock pot, bring 2 quarts of water to a boil; add beans and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, then let stand, covered, for 1 hour.
Drain.

title: cherry berry pie
directions: Drain cherries and berries, reserving 1 cup of their juices. Set fruit aside.
Combine sugar, juices and cornstarch in pan. Cook until it boils for 1 minute; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, almond extract and food coloring.
Fold in fruit; cool slightly.
Place one crust on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Add fruit, then other crust.
Cut slits in top of crust. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: caramelized onion tart
directions: Thaw puff pastry at room temperature.
Cook onions in hot oil in a large skillet over low heat, stirring often, 30 to 35 minutes or until onion is caramel colored.
Stir in salt and set mixture aside.

title: favorite squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with salt, pepper and sugar in water in saucepan until tender; drain.
Saute onion and carrot in butter in skillet. Add to squash 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: pepperoni-pizza casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in skillet over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until meat crumbles and is browned.
Drain well. Stir in sauce, salt, macaroni and 1 cup cheese.

Spoon into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange the pepperoni over the top. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle on the remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted and browned.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese, add dissolved gelatine.
Mix well, add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased cold mold and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: sore loser's polish sausage soup
directions: Film a heavy Dutch oven or stockpot with bacon drippings.
Add onions and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add broth, beer, sauerkraut, tomatoes, brown sugar and red pepper flakes.
(Don't add salt. There's plenty in the sauerkraut and broth.)
Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: simple cherry salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion slowly until the bacon is brown, but not crisp and the onion is clear (at least 10 minutes).
Add the drained clams (save juice) and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Sift flour over clams and stir until blended.
Add clam juice, half and half and milk and stir well.
Add diced potatoes; cover pan and simmer until potatoes are done, but still firm.
Stir periodically.
Add butter and simmer 3 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Can serve immediately, but is best the next day. Cool; refrigerate overnight, then reheat and serve with crackers.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spray Pam in bottom of 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Pour rhubarb, Jell-O and sugar ingredients into pan; spread even layer to cover entire bottom of pan.
Pour cake mixture into pan and be sure to cover entire bottom layer.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool and leave cake in pan.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip topping.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix together and put in greased (Pam) muffin pan.
Cook in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Place sugar, shortening and salt in large bowl.
Pour boiling water over sugar mixture and stir well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in eggs.
Sprinkle yeast over lukewarm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir well and add to sugar mixture.
Add flour; mix well with wooden spoon.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator for 2 hours or more.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: corn soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add corn and cook slowly until nearly done.
Add meat.
Cook until meat is tender and soup is thick. Add no salt while cooking.
Each individual should salt to his own taste when served.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together with the cream cheese. Delicious on chips or crackers!

title: granny walker's whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar
together.
Add
eggs
one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake in Bundt or similar pan for 1 hour
and 45
minutes at 325°, but check for doneness after 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Put in a 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over. Bake 1 hour at 275° to 350°.

title: spinach onion dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In 10 to 12-inch skillet, cook hamburger, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are softened. Drain and discard fat.
Add potatoes, tomato, chili powder, coriander and water.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: vanilla wafer pile
directions: Cream oleo and sugar and put aside.
Drain pineapple and add nuts.
Mix these ingredients with oleo and sugar; cream together. Lay mixture on wafers, cover it with another wafer, keep alternating mixture and wafers until three layers of wafers are made.
Ice cookie with Cool Whip.
Put coconut all over cookie. Let set in refrigerator for 2 whole days.
Cookie will be soft.

title: low-fat sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl; knead well and make into sausage patties. Pan-fry in nonstick pan or bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tex-mex turkey bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Combine baking mix and 1/2 cup water. Stir until soft dough forms. Press dough in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook turkey in a large nonstick skillet until brown. Stir in taco seasoning mix (dry) and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon mixture over dough. Combine spinach, Ricotta cheese and onion.
Spread over turkey mixture. Combine Cheddar cheese, sour cream and eggs.
Spoon evenly over spinach mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 cup Carnation milk. Spread 1/2 to 3/4 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: french onion soup(famous-barr)
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick.
Melt oleo and saute onions slowly for 1/2 hour in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients except bouillon.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add bouillon and simmer 2 hours (add wine toward end).
Adjust color to a rich brown with Kitchen Bouquet.
Salt to taste.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs and onion soup mix. Mix thoroughly and shape into small/medium meatballs. In large skillet over medium heat, gently brown the meatballs and set aside. In large saucepan, combine brown sugar, flour, water, vinegar, chili sauce and soy sauce. Mix thoroughly. Add meatballs and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: orange froth
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately.

title: apple-nut torte
directions: Add sugar to well beaten eggs;
beat with electric mixer until thick
and
light,
about 5
minutes at high speed.
Sift together flour,
baking powder and salt; fold into egg mixture. Lightly mix in
apples
and
pecans.
Grease
bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour
in
batter
and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40
to
45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut
in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix in a bowl the cream cheese, onion, green pepper, pineapple and 1 cup crushed almonds.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll balls in remaining 1 cup almonds.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.

title: broiled cheese sandwiches
directions: Cheeses must be at room temperature.
Combine ingredients. Spread on English muffins and place under broiler until browned.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix and pack the first 3 ingredients as crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake crust 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Whip cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar until creamy.
Put this second mixture on top of crust.
Beat pudding and milk together and spoon on top.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat slightly to mix the eggs, sugar and salt.
Scald milk (heat until a crinkly film forms on top).
Stir in egg mixture. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into 6 custard cups or a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and set in a pan of hot water 1 inch deep. Sprinkle a little nutmeg over the top of custard.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife blade inserted 1 inch from edge of dish comes out clean.
Remove from heat and allow to cool at room temperature.
Serve warm or chilled.
Refrigerate remainder.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix together in electric frypan.
Cook, covered, for 4 minutes at 350°.
Put in freezer bags.
Do not cool first.
Freeze immediately.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine oats and orange juice; stir well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, soda, oil and egg; mix well.
Stir in blueberries. Spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Blend 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: anytime soup
directions: Cook for 10 minutes and do not let it cook any longer.
Add
a pinch of red pepper and stir well.
Serves 12 people.
Enjoy.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Wash and bake potatoes until tender (400 for 1 1/2 hours). Allow potatoes to cool, then cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell. Put pulp in mixing bowl. Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add potato pulp, along with sour cream, milk, salt, and pepper. Beat with mixer until creamy. Stir in cheese.
Stuff potato shells with mixture and place in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with more cheese and bacon bits if desired. Bake at 350 for 20-30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put mixture into an ungreased, shallow baking dish.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chuck wagon surprise
directions: Saute burger, onion and bell pepper.
Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until hot.

title: microwave tomatoes parmesan
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and place in a 2-quart glass casserole. Combine the remaining ingredients and spoon over tomatoes.
Cook on HIGH for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Cook another 4 to 5 minutes, checking often for doneness.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Brown bacon and onion in pot; drain.
Add stock; bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms; cook until tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cut bones from pork chops.
Brown and put in casserole.
Mix together 1/2 cup cheese, soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over pork chops.
Add hash browns to the top and rest of cheese, then French fried onions.
Bake 90 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix apples and cranberries together.
Place in baking dish. Mix all dry ingredients together and add melted diet margarine. Spread topping over mixture and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook all macaroni, then drain. Mix together browned sausage, hamburger, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then 1/2 pasta, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cheese. Repeat with another layer of remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, celery, salt, mustard powder, onion powder and black pepper.
Gently stir in mayonnaise and lemon juice, also pickle and eggs.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix in order and pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press half the crumb mixture evenly in bottom of square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Place marshmallows, chocolate, shortening and water in saucepan; cook over low heat until melted and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla; beat until mixture starts to lose gloss.
Use immediately.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to strawberries.
Bake in 3 bread loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Test with a toothpick.

title: deviled dip
directions: Put all in blender and blend until smooth.

title: heath bar pudding
directions: Bake brownies.
Make mousse, following directions on box. Crush Heath bars that have been frozen into a large glass bowl. Crumble half of brownies.
Pour 1 box of mousse over brownies.
Use half of crumbled Heath bars.
Sprinkle over mousse.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic.
Form mixture into meatballs.
Mix catsup, beer and water, then add meatballs.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: wonton chips
directions: Brush wonton skins or tortillas with melted margarine.
Cut into 8 triangles.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt or cinnamon-sugar. Bake on lightly sprayed sheet until crisp
at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Gradually add flour and vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: planet(pizza)
directions: Place roll dough on cookie sheet; flatten to form rectangle. Spread tomato sauce over dough evenly.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle oregano and cheese over mushrooms.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: llew's cran-chicken
directions: Place the chicken parts in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn the chicken and continue baking 1 more hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: nut tarts
directions: Mix together.
Roll mixture into little balls and press into ungreased small cupcake tins. Chill in refrigerator for a few minutes while making filling.

title: date balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and chopped dates until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring.
Cool.
Make into balls and lightly roll in confectioners sugar or coconut. (These keep nicely in a covered container).

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening; add milk.
Makes a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll 3/4-inch thick and cut.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: cherry streusel
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut shortening and butter into crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Stir in baking powder and baking soda.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Beat at low speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then turn to 400°.
Remove cake from oven; quickly spread cherry pie filling over top.
Cover with reserved crumbs that have been mixed with 1 tablespoon butter and nuts, as desired.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: kisses
directions: Add sugar to egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: jello delight(mold)
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple juice over low heat, stirring constantly.
In a separate bowl, boil water and mix in lemon gelatin; set aside to let cool.
In a large mixing bowl, mix softened cream cheese, pineapple and carrots.
Blend in marshmallow mixture and lemon gelatin.
Pour mixture into mold (remember to coat mold with cooking oil).
Put in refrigerator to thicken overnight.
Serves 6 to 8 (recipe can be doubled).

title: cheddar cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese in a bowl.
Add salt, paprika and flour 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Press through star tip of a cookie press onto a cookie sheet.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch lengths.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 1/2 dozen.

title: potato cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: fancy lemon squares
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add 2 cups flour, beating until blended.
Spread evenly in well-greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thick and blended.
Add lemon juice, remainder of flour and baking powder. Beat until well blended.
Pour mixture over baked crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until custard is set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick-a-licious cup-a-barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine water, chili sauce, sugar, lemon juice, mustard and Lipton Cup-a-Soup.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
For basting hamburgers, chicken, steaks, chops, etc.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup and beans with half of the onion rings in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: white salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: vinegar taffy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil over medium heat and stir constantly until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking to hard ball stage (260°) or until a small amount forms a hard ball in very cold water.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla and beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan. When cool enough to handle, pull with fingers until satiny and light-colored.
Pull into long strips 3/4-inch in diameter; cut into 1-inch pieces with scissors.
Wrap each piece in wax paper. Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: delicious white bread
directions: Scald milk. Add honey, salt and butter.
Add cold water to cool mixture. When lukewarm, add yeast. Stir to dissolve.

Add about 4 cups of flour. Stir with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually add 7 more cups of flour, mixing well. Turn out onto floured board with final 1 cup of flour and knead 10 minutes, using minimal extra flour.
Let rise in a greased bowl, covered, until doubled in size (about 1 hour).
Punch down. Shape into loaves.
Place in greased bread pans.
Let rise again about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped.
Makes 4 large or 6 smaller loaves.

title: italian chicken
directions: In a jar mix dressing, shoyu and sugar well.
Marinate overnight.
Grill on a hibachi.

title: olene's original carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots, raisins, coconut and pineapple chunks.
Mix together juice, mayonnaise and brown sugar.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge brownies
directions: In a large bowl combine box of dry mix, hot water, oil and eggs.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Immediately upon taking brownies out of oven, start to prepare fudge so you can spread it on while both are hot.

title: texas spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add soup and puree.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Grease large casserole dish and layer spaghetti, meat mixture and mushrooms and cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: beefy bean soup
directions: In a saucepan, simmer cabbage and onion in the water, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in the undrained beans, soup and mustard.
Stir in corned beef and heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Mix together fruits, sugar and brandy.
Let it sit for 3 or 4 days.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Mix all 7 remaining ingredients in small bowl to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over ground beef.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over toasted buns.

title: apple-cheese
directions: Place drained apples into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in flour and cheese.
Spread cheese mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in saucepan; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
After it begins to boil remove from heat and let cool. Add remaining ingredients and a pinch of salt.
Bake in a greased, floured 9x13 inch pan at 325° for 45-60 minutes.

title: school house salad dressing
directions: Mix. Best if refrigerated over night.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add milk.
Mix dry ingredients.
Beat in alternately with milk.
Dip in butter and then sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gold brick fudge
directions: Place margarine, marshmallow cream and chocolate chips in mixer bowl that won't break. Mix sugar and cream in pot. After it starts to boil rapidly, continue boiling for 9 minutes, stirring constantly. Start mixer at low speed and pour syrup over bowl contents. Beat until smooth. Add nuts. Pour into buttered pan and cool for 3 hours before cutting.

title: peach delight
directions: Press
pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar into a
9 x 13-inch pan and bake 5 minutes (400°).
Let cool.
Mix together 1
cup
sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on crust. Dissolve
jello
in
cups boiling water (juice from fruit
and enough water to make 1 cup).
Add to jello and let set
up some. Add fruit; spread on top of filling.
Refrigerate.
Any kind of fruit may be used with matching jello.

title: easy 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, water and corn sugar in top part of a double boiler.
Beat until sugar dissolves.
Place over top of boiling water and cook, beating constantly until stiff.
Remove from heat until cooled, fold in vanilla.

title: fish pie
directions: First:
Fry fish, then break it into bite size pieces.
Cut up onion and saute in butter, then add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Cook until thick, then add fish and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Then pour into your pie shell.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Melt margarine and spoon over crumbs.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes in 9-inch round dish. Cook on High for 1 minute.
Stir and cook another 2 minutes until thick.
Add potatoes.
Cook on High for 5 minutes, rotating once and spoon syrup over top.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and sugar until it holds a peak.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Place in oven; turn oven off.
Leave cookies in the oven overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place noodles in greased casserole.
Add tuna, half of cheese and soup; mix lightly with noodles.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together strawberries, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients into other mixture.
Add pecans (optional).
Stir, mixing all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: overnight caramel-pecan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in milk, 1/3 cup sugar, the oil, baking powder, salt, egg and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto well-floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)

title: steak with herb stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients except bouillon cube and mushrooms and put on steak.
Roll steak up and tie or skewer.
Put into pan.
Mix bouillon cube with water and pour over steak.
Cook about 2 hours at 325°.
Brown mushrooms in skillet and put over steak.

title: minnie kyttle's orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add grated rind and eggs.
Beat. Add orange juice alternately with dry ingredients.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Orange Frosting.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add melted chocolate, coffee and rum.
Stir in flour and walnuts; turn into pie shell.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup walnut halves.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in this order; mix well.
Let stand for 10 minutes; mix again, then fill containers.
Makes approximately 16 quarts.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Slice apples and place into the bottom crust.
In a small saucepan empty apple juice and tapioca.
Heat and stir with wire whisk until mixture thickens.
Add spices and pour immediately over apples.
Top with crust.
Prick with a fork.
Brush with milk. Bake for 40 minutes in a 400° preheated oven.

title: low cholesterol corn chowder
directions: In a heavy 6 qt.
Dutch oven, place potatoes which have been diced into 1 inch pieces, diced onion and salt.
Pour water into the pan until the vegetables are covered.
Boil until potatoes can be pierced with a fork.
Add the cans of corn with the liquid; stir.
Add the evaporated milk and skim milk, stir.
Add the diced deli ham; heat thoroughly.
Season to taste with pepper and paprika.

title: beef and cheese ball
directions: Cut beef and onions very fine.
Mix rest of ingredients and refrigerate a few hours.
Shape into ball.
Can roll in crushed cracker crumbs or chopped nuts.
This can be doubled.
Best if made the day before you plan to serve.

title: cooking bag chicken
directions: Place all in a cooking bag.
Close bag with tie provided. Shake; punch 6 holes in bag.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can also use this with pork chops.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, onions, raisins, bacon and pecans in large mixing bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl and pour over broccoli mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix everything together except pecans.
Put pecans on just before serving.

title: southern peach custard pie
directions: Crush the fresh peaches and measure.
Combine with the sugar. In a saucepan combine the milk and cornstarch and bring to boil. Cook for 2 minutes and pour slowly over peaches, beating hard to blend.
Add egg yolks and cinnamon.
Beat again and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until filling is firm.
A meringue may be added if desired.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in pretty glass bowl; set aside.
Mix oil, juice, water, garlic, salt and pepper in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Add parsley and red pepper, stirring to blend.
Yields 10 appetizer servings.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream cheese and margarine; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy and add vanilla, green food coloring and flour.
Put into a cookie press with the star mold and make ring of dough about 1-inch round.
Place red hots for berries and bake in 375° oven for 6 minutes.

title: vanilla almond coffee
directions: Pour the vanilla and almond extracts into coffee.
Cover and shake well to blend.
Brew as you normally would.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large soup pot.
Add garlic, onions, celery and parsley and cook until soft.
Stir in tomato paste, 10 cups of water, bouillon cubes, cabbage, carrots, salt (1 teaspoon), pepper and sage and bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add kidney beans, peas or beans and simmer, covered, until heated through.
Bring remaining 6 cups of water to a boil in separate pan.
Add macaroni and salt (1 teaspoon).
Boil, uncovered, for 7 minutes.
Drain and add to soup pot.
Whisk in cheese mixture from package.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fried round steak
directions: Wash and tenderize meat.
Mix flour and salt and then cover meat well.
Cut onion rings.
Preheat oil and fry meat over low flame.
When just about done, add onion rings and fry them.

title: amaretto cream
directions: Toast almonds, spread out on a 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Shake pan occasionally.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Combine the brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt.
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add soda and vanilla; beat.
Pour over popcorn.
Microwave a total of 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Stir about every 1 minute.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese (softened), Cool Whip, sour cream and whipping cream in large mixing bowl until well blended.
Add to mixture brown sugar until smooth, then Kahlua.

title: tater tot - hamburg
directions: Brown meat, onion and salt.
Put in heavy casserole, layering with potatoes and soup mixed with milk.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove cover.
Add French onions and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out pastry and place in pie pan. In large bowl, beat honey, butter and egg yolks together well. Dissolve cornstarch in buttermilk and add to butter mixture along with lemon juice and rind.
Mix in fruit.
Beat egg whites until stiff and then fold into rest of filling carefully.
Turn into unbaked pie crust, then sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 15 to 20 more minutes until set.
Cool before serving.

title: i ought to feel guilty cheesecake
directions: *Use 1 or a mixture of cottage cheese, tofu, cream cheese, yogurt cheese or white Cheddar.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl and mix up.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together twice the first 5 ingredients.
Mix well the sugar and oil.
Add grated carrots to oil and sugar mixture. Beat.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add 1 cup pecans to dry ingredients and add to the other mixture (optional).
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 35 minutes or longer.

title: christmas candy
directions: Shave small amounts of paraffin wax in with chopped almond bark.
Melt (over hot water).
Pour melted almond bark over other ingredients and mix well.

title: spiced cider
directions: Simmer ingredients for 10 minutes.
Strain and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip. Mix well; chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: iced orange cappuccino
directions: Place orange zest in bottom of coffeepot.
Brew coffee, using cold water and espresso; cool to room temperature.
Strain coffee and discard orange zest.
Stir in NutraSweet Spoonful and milk. Refrigerate until chilled.
Pour cappuccino into chilled tall glasses; spoon small dollop of whipped topping on each.
Sprinkle with cocoa, nutmeg or cinnamon.
Makes 8 servings (about 8 ounces each).

title: strawberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease sides of 9-inch square pan. Combine cookie mix, lemon peel and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add contents of buttery flavor packet from cookie mix and egg white. Press dough into the bottom of the pan.
Put preserves on top of dough and bake at 350° for 30 to 32 minutes.
Cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: bread machine apple-oat bread
directions: Follow instructions on your bread machine.

title: miss rosa's gingerbread
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Stir brown sugar into melted shortening, add molasses and unbeaten eggs.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and hot water alternately in small amounts, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into greased pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) about 25 minutes.
Makes one (10 x 10-inch) cake.

title: mom's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 2 pieces of ham and 2 pieces cheese in spread out chicken breasts.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake and place in oblong pan.
Mix soups and wine together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Stir together eggs, bananas, flour, soda and salt.
Add to oleo and sugar mixture.
Then add pecans, chocolate chips and maraschino cherries.
These are optional. Bake in well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.
I use 2 little foil pans.
These freeze very well.
I usually double recipe and bake in 3 foil pans measuring 4 x 8-inch at the top.

title: chocolate philly fudge
directions: You will need a shallow greased pan.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix together well.
Make into small balls. Place onto an ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Press each with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until a pale tan color. With a spatula, gently remove to a cool place.

title: parmesan creamed spinach
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender, add spinach and cook until thoroughly heated.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Add flour, cook, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese and spinach mixture, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Can be served immediately, or placed in greased casserole and reheated later.
Do not overcook spinach.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except potato chips or bread crumbs.
Top with crumbs and some melted margarine before baking. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (glass dish) at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes (uncovered).

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers and cover with ice cubes. When ready to serve, drain well and cover with the sauce.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, chives or green onions, vinegar and salt and pepper. Stir into cucumbers and serve.

title: syrian apple cake
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and let stand one hour. Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; pour over apple mixture.
Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until pick comes out clean.

title: mom's vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let set a couple of hours to blend flavors. Serve with all types of vegetables.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: fudge topping
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add milk; cook slowly until thick.

title: creamed peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend flour and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Mix peas, salt and pepper and stir.

title: pizza boats
directions: Cook ground beef in pan, drain off fat.
Mix sauce, cheese and mushrooms in with ground beef, heat on low until cheese has melted, stirring often.
Unwrap bread, cut in 4 parts, then cut each piece sideways, layer the sauce evenly on bottom part of bread.
Place the top part on.
Wrap in foil, lay on cookie sheet, bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and vegetable oil.

title: salsa soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Heat through and serve.

title: zemakove placky(potato pancakes)
directions: This recipe was brought into Burleson County by the Czech-Moravian immigrants in the middle 1800's.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, sprinkle the following on top:

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 375° until brown.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger. Chill dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, pineapple and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and flatten with spoon dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: monkie cake
directions: Put cinnamon and sugar in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters and shake in cinnamon mixture.
Layer in a tube pan. Layer one can at a time, sprinkling raisins and nuts over each can.
Bring to a boil 1 1/4 sticks margarine and leftover cinnamon and sugar.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Use solid bottom tube pan.

title: deans cookies
directions: Crumble up the graham crackers into small crumbs.
(I usually put them in a Ziploc bag and roll with a rolling pin.)
After they're crumbled, pour into a medium bowl; add condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into cake pan (sprayed with nonstick spray).
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: blueberry peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, combine peaches and blueberries. Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, flour and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a small bowl and mix well.
Add to peaches and blueberries, tossing to mix.
Combine oats, remaining 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
With a pastry blender, cut in margarine until crumbly, then sprinkle over fruit. Bake for 25 minutes or until fruit is just tender and mixture is bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stew
directions: Brown stew meat.
Add remaining ingredients; cook in crock-pot 5 to 6 hours or on the stove in heavy pan 3 hours.
Or bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix vanilla, 1 cup sugar and cream cheese and fold in Cool Whip.
Put mixture in two baked pie shells.
(Before baking pie shells, press pecans into them and bake.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature (overnight); mix cheeses together, then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into two balls.
Refrigerate one hour or longer.
Roll in chopped pecans or parsley.

title: ham and cheese omelet
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer bread and cheese slices and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Add ham, mustard and pepper.
Beat eggs, milk and rest of cheese.
Pour over all. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, thoroughly combine potatoes, sugar, salt, spices and flavoring.
Add eggs; beat vigorously until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: fruity cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, orange peel, almond extract and ginger. Beat until smooth.
Place 1/2 cup crushed cereal in serving dish. Spoon cheese mixture on top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cereal over cheese spread and serve with fruit slices, crackers and cookies.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: roasted rock cornish hens
directions: In a glass bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
With a large sharp knife or poultry shears, remove the backbone from each hen by cutting down either side of the bone.
Halve the hens and place in a large nonreactive bowl.
Pour marinade over the birds and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: broccoli cheese noodle soup
directions: In large kettle, saute onions (add water instead of butter), add remaining ingredients except cheese and milk. Cook over low to medium heat until noodles are done, add the cheese and milk. Stir and cook until cheese is melted. Total cooking time approximately 20 minutes.

title: onion cheese biscuit loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a small skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix together flour, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar, butter and nuts.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, 2/3 cup powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat pudding and milk together for 2 minutes.
Spread mixture over cheese mixture. Spread with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: Combine all but catsup.
Press into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High, 8 1/2 minutes. Spread catsup over top.
Recover with plastic wrap and microwave 8 1/2 minutes.
Conventional, 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Add flour and wheat germ.
Mix well.
Add baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Mash bananas and add to sugar and shortening.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: stuffed apple salad
directions: Cut apples in half crosswise; core each with a sharp knife or melon baller, leaving a 1-inch hole in center.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine coconut, graham cracker crumbs, walnuts and melted butter in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Press 2/3 of mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, spice and salt.
Spoon over coconut mixture.
Sprinkle remaining coconut mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread on tortilla.
Roll up.
Chill overnight.
Cut in pieces the next day.

title: ritz cracker peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar and evaporated milk over low heat three minutes. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and cracker crumbs. Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Beat cheeses in medium bowl with electric medium speed until well blended.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Mix soup and sour cream (and cheese, if using). Mix in squash and onion.
Cook stuffing in butter.
Spread stuffing on bottom of baking dish.
(Save some stuffing for top.)
Spoon squash mixture over stuffing.
Add remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: czar czandwich
directions: Spread bread with butter; place on broiler-proof pan.
Top each slice with sliced hard-cooked egg, then with mushrooms. Spoon 1 tablespoon salad dressing over each slice of bread; top with 3 half slices of bacon.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat, 4 to 5 minutes or until bacon crisps.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sen. muriel humphrey's dinner in a dish
directions: Saute onion and peppers in 4 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Add beef, salt and pepper and cook over high heat 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool 5 minutes.
Mix in eggs.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer ingredients:
1 cup corn on bottom, followed by 1/2 the meat mixture and half of the tomatoes.
Repeat that order of layers.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Dot with 2 teaspoons butter.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: crescent beef and bacon sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon.
Add beef and onion.
Brown and drain.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.

title: dirt(ingredients for two 8-inch flowerpots or 1 large)
directions: Crush Oreos.
Place 1/3 of Oreos in bottom of "pot."
In large bowl combine cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. In medium bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Then fold mixes together, then fold in 1/3 Oreos.
Put mixture into "pot." Then put remaining Oreos on top.
Use plastic or candy flowers to decorate (garnish).
Serve with a "garden spade."

title: stuffed peppers 2
directions: Mix chopped meat with salt and pepper.
Add onion, mushrooms and soup.
Fill peppers and put in casserole with rest of mixture around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
In place of tomato soup, tomato juice can be used.
Celery can be added if desired.

title: pineapple-lemon salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat pineapple juice.
Add dry Jell-O. Remove from heat.
When dissolved, add cream cheese and pineapple. Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a "well" in middle of bowl.
Pour in all other ingredients.
Stir with spoon until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water and set aside.
Mix other ingredients; add yeast mixture.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 400°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for 1 cup white sauce and hard-boiled egg, and form a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
To the other cup of white sauce, add chopped hard-boiled egg and serve over the Salmon Loaf.

title: fruit slush punch
directions: Put bananas, lemon juice and strawberries in blender. Blend until smooth. Add to thawed grape juice and pineapple juice in a large bowl. Heat sugar and 6 cups water until sugar dissolves (do not boil). Add to fruit mixture. Mix well and freeze.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Partially cook approximately 6 slices of bacon per can of green beans.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut each slice of bacon in half.
Wrap each 1/2 slice bacon around a bundle of green beans; secure with a toothpick.
Place bundles in a baking dish. Generously dribble the dressing over all the bundles to marinate them for several hours or overnight.
Cook bundles for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Can substitute a variety of dressings.

title: momma's corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, salt, sugar, butter, milk and eggs.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into corn mixture.
Pour into greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the custard is firm.

title: pecan cheese balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape into small balls and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Chill and serve with toothpicks and crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scallops with vegetables
directions: In a small bowl, combine soy sauce and dry sherry; mix chicken broth and cornstarch.
Mix well and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add carrots, zucchini, mushrooms and green and red pepper and stir-fry 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove and set aside.
Wipe out pan.
Heat remaining tablespoon oil in frypan and saute garlic and ginger 1 minute.
Add scallops and stir-fry until they become opaque.
Return vegetables to frypan.
Add baby corn (cut into 1-inch pieces) and reserved soy sauce mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Sprinkle scallions and serve over rice.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Add more butter on top of biscuits.
Add more garlic powder and more cheese.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: low-fat cherry delight
directions: Line a casserole dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Add margarine and smooth out.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes and allow to cool.

title: buns
directions: Mix water and sugar; boil for 5 minutes.
Add shortening. Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and salt.
Dissolve dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add to other ingredients.
Add flour in steps. Use electric mixer as long as possible, then mix with a wooden spoon.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown outside of roast in large pot with margarine. After all sides are brown, remove from stove. Place roast in crock-pot. Add water to cover roast. Add soup mix (Lipton). Salt and pepper to taste and cook on high for 4 to 5 hours. If planning on leaving crock-pot, cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Combine the soup, sage and sour cream.
Pour over potato mixture. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rice green chili bake
directions: Cook rice.
Cook zucchini until crisp-tender.
Set aside. Place cooked rice in 3-quart casserole. Cover with chilies. Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and put zucchini over cheese. Add tomato and season with salt.
Combine sour cream, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt, green pepper and onion and spread over tomato. Scatter remaining cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: window and mirror cleaner
directions: No general rule can be given for bathing; age and state of health are all important considerations in determining the kind of bath to be taken.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Combine and cream well the first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt, then add the milk alternately with the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Add flavorings last.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until cake tests done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain and save juice.
In a small pan, combine margarine, onions, garlic salt, Worcestershire and flour.
Stir over medium heat until onions wilt.
Add milk and spinach juice. Grate cheese and add.
Stir until melted.
Put spinach in a casserole dish, pour sauce over and stir.
Sprinkle with croutons and bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: hamburg chop suey
directions: For every 1 cup of rice there should be added 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cover and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Thaw frozen chopped spinach.
Put in strainer.
Squeeze to remove water.
Combine hot water and lemon gelatin.
Dissolve gelatin, then add cold water and vinegar.
Let set until mixture is syrupy.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Spread on buns.

title: taco soup
directions: In 3 or 4-quart kettle, lightly brown beef and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, corn, tomato sauce, water, mushrooms, plus taco and chili seasonings.
Bring to a boil and simmer at least 45 minutes.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Stir in frozen fruit and break apart as fruit starts to thaw.
Put in refrigerator while breaking up angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Layer as follows in a trifle bowl or a 9 x 13-inch pan:

title: pineapple or applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together then stir in wet ingredients. Do not have to use mixer.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Leave the cake in the pan and pour the hot icing over the cake while the cake is still hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, salt, flour, baking powder, nutmeg, butter and corn.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Place pan of corn pudding in shallow pan of water.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Makes 6 servings.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients with electric mixer.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in casserole. Top with more crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab or shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Heat 2 quarts water to dissolve sugar.
Mix all ingredients. Freeze part to add to liquid part later to make slush.
Makes 3 1/2 gallons.
Triple recipe makes 10 1/2 gallons.
Ten and one-half gallons serve approximately 200 people.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in oleo, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and beaten egg until thoroughly combined.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: slow cooker green beans
directions: Put all ingredients in kettle and let steam.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Place chicken in large pot and cover with water. (Add onions, celery, carrots, parsley, salt and pepper for a rich broth.) Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer for an hour. Remove chicken. Cool and shred. Saut onions and green chilies in 2 tablespoons butter. Add cream cheese and chicken. Put 1 heaping spoonful on each tortilla and roll up. Place side by side in shallow glass dish. Cover with cheese, then cream. Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly and lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Puree tomatoes in the blender; mix in Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Brown chicken in margarine in large skillet.
Put chicken in shallow baking dish; pour tomato sauce over.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Place cheese on chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Stir together peanut butter, 1/2 cup melted butter and confectioners sugar.
Press mixture into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate pieces and stir together with remaining tablespoon of melted butter. Spread on top.
Set in refrigerator for 10 minutes to set chocolate.
Store at room temperature.
Cut into small squares.

title: favorite cheese balls
directions: Blend cheese and butter with electric mixer.
Add sauces and soup mix, continuing to blend.
Shape into ball and place on aluminum foil.
Cover cheese ball with almonds.
Wrap loosely with foil and refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll into small balls. Make these so small you think they're too small because they expand quite a bit. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onions in butter with bay leaf (to be removed before pureeing) until onions are translucent.
Add the chopped broccoli, water or stock and seasonings.
Cook about 10 minutes covered until broccoli is tender, but still bright green.
Puree little by little with milk in the blender.
Make sure the mixture is absolutely smooth.
Whisk in sour cream or yogurt.
Heat gently and serve right away.
Top with minced scallions.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
While stirring, add flour and baking soda.
Cook 12 minutes, then add Hershey's Kiss. Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer or until cookies are done. Temperature: 350°.

title: breakfast pie with potatoes
directions: Combine sausage and potatoes with cheese in a pie shell. In bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over sausage, potatoes and cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In bowl, mix flour, salt, sugar and baking soda.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Mix well.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Add boiled mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while still warm.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well. Add flour, soda and salt.
Add coconut and then oatmeal.
Mix. Dough is stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; spray cookie sheet with Pam or grease with margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Let cool and pour over 2 cups fresh strawberries.
Pour in pie shell.
Let stand until firm.
Add Cool Whip.

title: heavenly fruit salad dressing
directions: In a small saucepan, mix the eggs with sugar, orange juice and vinegar, stirring constantly until mixture is thick.
Stir in butter and cool, then pour in sour cream.
Excellent with summer fruits or fruit salads.

title: crescent wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough and cut into lengthwise 1/4-inch strips. Wrap around sausages, leaving ends exposed. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
These are delicious cold too!
