title: pumpernickel bread(round loaf)
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add other ingredients to spinach. Cut out center of bread; fill with spinach mixture.

title: fancy lace cookies
directions: Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, sweetener, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat well.
Stir in butter, rolled oats, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: twinkie de-lite
directions: Slice Twinkies horizontally and line the bottom of the dish with them.
Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Spread pineapple over Twinkies.
Place bananas over pineapple.
Drizzle 1 to 3 tablespoons pineapple juice over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Chill and serve.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Pan-fry lightly with oil the beef cubes until brown.
Remove from pan.
Place beef in a casserole dish.
Mix and pour the rest of the ingredients over beef.
Bake at 320° for 3 hours.
Use over rice or noodles.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in oil; add meat and seasonings.
Brown lightly. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add soups; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water.
Drain and add to sauce.
Mix well.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans, onions and Creole seasoning (to taste) until almost done. Add sausage. Cook until beans are tender. Serve in bowls over rice.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dice apples with the skin on or off and add nut meats, celery and optional raisins or dates.
Add salad dressing and mix well. Chill for a short time before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add pineapple with juice.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 375° until brown and juice has bubbled through.

title: chicken gravy
directions: Combine flour and skim milk, beating until smooth, or shake mixture in tightly capped jar.
Gradually add to chicken broth or essence in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add seasoning; reduce heat and continue to cook, stirring, 5 minutes longer.
Yield:
1 cup.
Approximate calories/serving:
1 cup = 80, 1 tablespoon = 5.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion; drain.
Place in crock-pot along with remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 hours on high.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture firmly in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; beat in milk, vanilla and egg, mixing well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting.
Refrigerate leftovers.
These bars freeze well.
The entire pan of bars contains 5,260 calories and cost about $7.00 to make, but it's worth it!

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Stir in flour, cherries, nuts and coconut.
Form into 2 rolls (each 2 inches in diameter and 8 inches long).
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Crunch up noodles before opening package, then open and set beef flavoring packets aside. Mix first 4 ingredients.

title: chicken and rice(microwave)
directions: In
a
quart
casserole or country cooker, mix rice, soup and water.	Place the split chicken breasts on top (thick part to the outside).
Cook on High for 15 minutes, then 20 to 25 minutes on level 3 or on simmer.
Serves 4.

title: batter for fish or onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika in a bowl, then pour in a can of beer and mix.
Dip the fish or onion rings in flour, then in the batter and cook in a large, high sided skillet or fryer in about an inch of hot oil.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; drain grease off.
Add chicken gumbo soup, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slightly grease casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, mixed vegetables and hamburger.
Salt each layer; mix soup and milk. Pour over the top of vegetables and meat.
Grate cheese on top and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, covered.
Take cover off the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: sausage krispies balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls, size of a marble.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oatmeal; add melted butter and stir until crumbly.
Measure about 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Press firmly to cover bottom.
Combine preserves and water, mixing well.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over preserves.
Pat firmly to make top even.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 23 minutes or until top is very light brown.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook pudding on stove as directed on box.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add cooked pudding to dry cake mix.
Pour mixture into cake pan.
Sprinkle chips and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing. Stir in peppers.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain any grease off.
Cook onion and hot pepper with meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about
1 1/2 hours on medium heat.
Stir often.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towels.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Place on grill over a medium fire (ash-covered charcoal) for about 30 to 45 minutes, turning frequently.

title: pineapple-orange refrigerator cake
directions: Do not drain oranges.
Mix all ingredients together well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: rich muffins
directions: Combine eggs, oil and milk together.
Mix dry ingredients together and blend slowly with liquid ingredients; mix only until all dry particles are moist.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
May add fresh fruit, chocolate chips or nuts.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt gradually.
Add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until mixture begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove chicken.
Add bouillon cubes and spaghetti; cook until tender.
Drain, but do not rinse.

title: pecan ball cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and chopped pecans.
Mix thoroughly and form into small balls.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Make the balls as small as possible).

title: hoggie
directions: Roll out bread roll. Brown hamburger. Layer each ingredient on the bread roll. When all ingredients are used up, fold your bread up like a napkin. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and pour over 8 ounces cream cheese.
Eat with party crackers.

title: cracker torte
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Combine egg whites, vanilla, salt and sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in cracker crumb mixture and nuts.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool. Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: french dressing recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients in quart jar.
Cover tightly and shake to blend.
Store in refrigerator.
Remove garlic when serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add sifted ingredients; mix 2 minutes. Add mashed bananas, sour milk and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: new year's day black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Cook pork, peas and water for 45 minutes on low heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for sausage. Cover.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour on low heat.
Add sausage.
Cook uncovered 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces; place in a saucepan.
Cover with water; cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Make a white sauce from the butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Stir constantly until thickened.
In a 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer the cabbage, sauce and cheese.
Repeat twice; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cold vinegar pickles
directions: Mix a paste of the spices and mix into cider vinegar.
Use whole small cucumbers and leave the stem in place. If large cucumbers, after washing, cut them into spears.
After the cucumbers are clean, place in a large jar or crock.
Pour the vinegar mixture over the cucumbers and weight them down with a plate or non metal object to keep the cucumbers below the brine.

title: travel cakes
directions: Pour into cupcake cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: grape pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, salt and milk to pulp.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue and bake until lightly browned.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix crackers with 1/2 stick butter.
Form crust in pie plate. Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Place onions on crust.
Pour egg mixture over onions and crust.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Prepare the following topping and spread over mixture, then bake for another 10 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and mix all other ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: florida pork chops
directions: In skillet, cook chops in oil over medium heat.
When chops are lightly browned on both sides, drain off oil.
Place a green pepper ring on top of each chop; add orange juice mixed with steak sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Stir to mix.
Serve as a dip with sliced tart apple slices, such as Granny Smith or with apple chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together cauliflower, broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon. Mix well salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Combine with vegetables.
Serve immediately.

title: peppermint frozen dessert
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup of the water in 1-quart saucepan to soften.
Stir in sugar.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until dissolved (do not boil).
Remove from heat. In large mixing bowl, sprinkle milk powder over remaining 3 cups of water.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer, adding corn oil, corn syrup, sugar-gelatin mixture, vanilla and salt.
Chill about 1 hour.
Freeze in electric or hand crank freezer following manufacturer's directions.
When partially frozen, add 1/3 cup of the crushed peppermint candy and continue freezing.
Stir in remaining peppermint candy.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: ham rolls
directions: Take one slice of ham (dry off juice). Spread cream cheese. Roll up and insert 3 toothpicks. Cut in between or leave whole for those hungry kids.

title: super sauced pork tidbits
directions: Shape bulk sausage into small balls.
Fry until evenly browned.
Combine applesauce, spices and coloring; heat until hot. Place sauce in chafing dish.
Add browned sausage balls.
Place fancy toothpicks in each one of the sausage balls.
This way, your guests can take one or several with no trouble.
Makes 50 sausage balls.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl; beat until foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in medium bowl; mix well. Add to zucchini mixture; mix well.
Fold in walnuts and raisins gently.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until loaves test done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Take the separated chicken wings and dip in egg and milk mixture, then into flour.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in baking dish and pour sauce on top of wings. Bake at 350° for about an hour. Baste frequently.

title: treasure cake
directions: Place in 9-inch greased pan and bake in moderate oven.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add onions, milk and egg.
Drop by spoon into deep hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: snow peak frosting
directions: Heat syrup to boiling point. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add salt. Slowly pour corn syrup over beaten egg whites, continuing to beat until mixture is fluffy and hangs in peaks from beater.
Fold in vanilla.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix wet ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients. Fold in cranberries.
Spoon into greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix real good and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Mix well pineapple juice, lemonade and water.
Add ginger ale just before serving; stir in well.
Add sugar to taste, if desired.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers, discard seed and membranes.

Place peppers in boiling water and cook 5 minutes, invert and drain. Cook sausage in skillet until done, drain off grease, chop fine. Add rice, onion, cheese, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, mix well. Stuff mixture into peppers.
Bake covered at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add bread crumbs, paprika and thyme. Set aside.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan and blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add liquid from potatoes and 1 cup milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add shredded cheese and cook until melted.
Stir in ham.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice, and set pineapple aside. In a saucepan, combine gelatin, water and reserved juice.
Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until syrupy, about 30 minutes.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy, stir in gelatin mixture, nuts, marshmallows, and pineapple.
Fold in cream and transfer to a 1 qt. serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours until set.
Serves about 8.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Place all ingredients except chicken in a blender.
Liquify. Pour marinade over chicken in a bowl and marinate at least 30 minutes, mixing occasionally.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and sour milk or buttermilk alternately.
Add nuts and fruits; mix well.
Chill dough for several hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: christmas pecan cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add lemon juice, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix in raisins, nuts and flour alternately. Spoon into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.

title: red pepper sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables, do not brown! Simmer until soft.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir, add broth and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Cool, put in blender and puree.
Put back in pan, simmer 15 more minutes or until slightly thickened. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: seafood and sausage stew
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling.

Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove cover. Cook, turning sausages frequently, until water evaporates and sausages are browned, about 20 minutes. Remove sausages to paper towels to drain. Cut each sausage diagonally in half.
Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.
In remaining drippings over medium heat, cook onion until tender.
Add 1 cup water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Add potatoes and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: jello surprise
directions: Combine jello and water.
Stir in vanilla ice cream.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: apple oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking powder and soda.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and margarine. Add more buttermilk if batter is too thick. Stir in grated apples.
Makes 12 to 14 small pancakes.

title: california marinade
directions: Mix.
Cover meat or chicken with sauce and refrigerate for 24 to 36 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and flour; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in buttered dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut marshmallows in four squares and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler until creamy. Remove from heat.
Mix in condensed milk, vanilla and pecans. Pour mixture over marshmallows; let cool several hours or overnight before cutting in squares.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil until tender the amount of carrot that you want.
Drain and while hot mix in 1 to 2 tablespoons of orange or kumquat marmalade.
A small amount of butter may also be used.

title: chocolate mounds cake
directions: Put in saucepan; heat until marshmallows melt.
Spread on hot cake after cake has baked.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles as directed.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil and butter.
In another small bowl, beat egg with fork.
Dip chicken in egg, then into bread crumb mixture, coating evenly.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add coated chicken.
Cook 5-7 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Add marinara sauce and water to skillet.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low. Cook 12-15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Sprinkle each piece of chicken with 1 Tbsp. mozzarella cheese.
Cover, cook 2-3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: california salad
directions: Toss ingredients together in bowl.
Just before serving, toss with dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour slowly with cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape into medium size balls, then roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake in oven at 400° for at least 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken hawaii
directions: Place chicken in a large bowl.
Combine soy sauce, onion and ginger.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for at least 1 hour, turning chicken to coat all sides.
Drain chicken and coat with cornstarch, reserving sauce.
Place margarine in large baking dish.
Add chicken, skin side down.
Bake for 40 minutes (until bottom side is well browned) at 350°.
Turn chicken over.
Combine pineapple chunks and liquid, lemon juice and reserved sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes more or until tender.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix well and drop through funnel into hot oil.
Crisscross to keep cake together.
Serve with powdered sugar or plain.

title: barbecue chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Dip over chicken continuously until dip is gone.

title: applesauce meatballs(easy)
directions: Mix meat, applesauce, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Form small balls (walnut size).
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil.
Place in shallow casserole.
Pour catsup and water mixture over.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes at 350°.
Stir once or twice while baking. Serve alone or over noodles.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix
graham
crackers, fruit, raisins and nuts in large pan. Melt
marshmallows
in
milk and pour over first mixture and mix well.
Press tight in lined loaf pan.
Place in icebox for 2 to 3 days.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients and sugar together.
Add egg, milk, onion and shortening.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop from tablespoon into deep hot fat; fry until golden brown.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil, peel and mash potato.
While still hot, start adding sugar and vanilla.
Keep adding sugar until like pie dough.
Put powdered sugar on wax paper or pie board.
Mix candy well and roll just like pie crust.
Spread peanut butter and roll like jelly roll (about 1/4-inch thick).
Chill for a few hours and cut 1/4-inch thick.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Stir together sugar, eggs and vanilla with spoon (do not beat hard).
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool, cut in squares.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Mix well, then add shrimp.
Leave in marinade for at least 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Grill until bright orange, then brush with marinade again.
Grill 5 additional minutes, then serve hot. Yield:
4 servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts; press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: cool tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni (about 4 cups).
In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add macaroni; toss to coat.
Add tuna and vegetables; toss gently.
Cover; refrigerate until cool, at least 4 hours.
Makes 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and onions in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to soup to cover potatoes. Cover top of mixture completely with slices of American cheese.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Blend together Cool Whip and cheese, then add to other mix and blend, then add 2 cans mandarin oranges and blend all together.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix everything, except eggs, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased tube pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and enjoy!

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place all ingredients,
except
pork chops, in blender. Blend on high speed until
sauce is mixed and smooth, about 30 seconds. Place
chops
in
regular
or
electric
frying
pan preferably, and pour sauce over all.
Marinate chops, covered, for
hours. Bring sauce to bubble, then simmer on low heat for 45 minutes. Makes about 1 3/4 cups marinade.

title: quick stuffed cabbage
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Chop cabbage in small pieces.
Put in bottom of baking dish.
Add meat mixture on top of cabbage.
In small pan, beat water, soup and sauce; pour over mixture.
Enjoy!

title: ann's yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix milk, hot water, sugar and salt together and dissolve yeast into mixture and let cool.
Add 3 cups flour and stir.
Beat egg; add to mixture and stir.
Add 3 cups flour and oil and mix well.

title: dessert grillers
directions: Arrange fruit on 12 wooden skewers.
Spread margarine evenly on both sides of pound cake slices.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl; sprinkle over cake slices.
Place cake on grill over hot coals or on rack of broiler pan.
Heat on both sides until lightly toasted.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip and fruit kabobs. Makes 12 servings.
(You may substitute fruit cocktail instead of the fruit kabobs, if you wish.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet or baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter and arrange drained pineapple in an attractive pattern on the butter-sugar coating.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack
okra,
onion, garlic, dill and one hot pepper (if desired)
in
pint
jars.
Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour hot liquid
over
okra
and seal.
Put sealed jars in oven at 250° for 10 minutes to seal good.
Cut oven off.

title: cranberry salad(regular or sugar free)
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
Grind cranberries, orange and apple in food processor.
Add to warm jello with walnuts and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine onions, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, avocados and taco sauce; set aside.
Brown meat; add beans and simmer 10 minutes. Combine Blue cheese mix with sour cream.
Add cooled, browned meat and beans to lettuce mixture.
Toss with Blue cheese mix and chips.
Serve.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; trim ends. Put mushrooms in water. Cook for 10 minutes. Boil; drain well. Mix marinade and pour over mushrooms. Bring back to a boil for 2 minutes. Store in plastic airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Tear the tortillas in half and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of meat mixture on top of tortillas. Repeat layer.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and clams. Drop from teaspoon into deep hot fat.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into chunks; press together on pizza pan to make crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 3 minutes, including juice from oranges.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed cheese
directions: Hollow out center of cheese round, leaving a shell 1/2-inch thick.
Set shell aside.
Shred cheese and set aside.
Combine refried beans and next 6 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until thoroughly heated.
Set aside.

title: peach or apple pie
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of baking dish; pour 1 large can of peaches and juice or 1 quart of apples.
If apples aren't sweetened, use 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Make a batter with remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over fruit; do not stir batter with fruit.
Bake at 350° until done, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat together until light and fluffy cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Line small cupcake tins with papers.
Place 1 teaspoon of crushed vanilla wafer in bottom of each paper cup. Fill cup 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until set.
Top with pie filling or preserves.
Makes 60 tarts.

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Mix.
Let stand overnight in tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely, 6 to 8 weeks.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, or until brown.
Cool.

title: healthy brown bread
directions: Fast, easy one bowl directions:
Put 4 cups of the water through the coffeemaker to heat.
Get small bowl or cup and put one half of a cup of the hot water in it and enough of the remaining one cup of cold water in it to make warm, but not hot.
Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Get a large plastic bowl, pour the 4 1/2 cups of hot water and the remaining cold water together in bowl.

Using a two-cup measuring cup, if possible, pour the oil first, then the molasses and honey (the oil coats the cup and keeps the molasses and honey from sticking on the cup) into the bowl, add the salt and stir mixture well.
Add the whole wheat flour gradually.
Mix in seeds.
Mix in remaining flour until your dough is soft but firm. Knead well and rub surface with a little oil.
Put cover on bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down and divide into three parts. Put in bread pans or cake pans for round loaves.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake until top is nicely browned.
Make sure you don't take out too soon.
Take out of pans and cool on racks, rub surface with stick of butter while hot and let cool (cover with cloth if desired).
Makes great bread; slices well, extremely healthy for snacks, sandwiches, toast, etc.
Three loaves lasts us only about 5 days or so.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chili and cheese spread. Cook over low heat, stirring often, until cheese has melted and mixture is heated thoroughly. Serve warm with chips.

title: caias (do-nuts)
directions: Combine rice, Bisquick, sugar and spices.

Mix eggs, milk and vanilla. Add to the dry ingredients and cooked rice mixture. Mix well and chill for 1 hour. heat oil to 400°. Drop the batter in the hot oil, 1 tablespoon at a time, and fry about 3 to 5 minutes. Make glaze of last 3 ingredients and spoon over hot Caias.

title: cornbread salad
directions: I cook both mixes together and bake in an iron skillet. Crumble cooked cornbread in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise and diced vegetables.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix.
Keep refrigerated. Drink 8 ounces per day.
(This is supposed to help arthritis and high cholesterol.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Separate biscuits from tubes and cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Use 1/2 of sugar and cinnamon mixture; dip 15 pieces in mixture and put in Bundt pan.

title: golden coconut mounds
directions: Start oven at 350°.
Lightly grease two cookie sheets.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat eggs with sugar just until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in coconut and flour all at once.
Drop mixture about 2 tablespoons at a time, 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Shape into peaked mounds.
Bake 10 to 18 minutes or until golden on top and bottom.
Makes 1 1/4 dozen.

title: spice pecans
directions: Mix egg, spices, salt and sugar in a bowl, then add pecans and stir until covered good with the mixture.
Spray cookie sheet with Baker's Joy.
Place pecans on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch; cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and lemon; stir. Add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill several hours.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with a few berries.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Thick with 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: rachel's one dish dinner
directions: Cook bell pepper and onion in small amount of oil and set aside.
Cook ground beef until all moisture is cooked out of it. Add bell pepper and onion to the meat, add red chili sauce and canned tomatoes.
Cook for an hour.
(This may be cooked a day ahead.)
Cook macaroni barely tender.
Add to mixture and sprinkle grated cheese over it.
Add olives around it before serving. Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with garlic bread and cole slaw.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: easy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix thawed souffle, bread crumbs, lemon juice, onions and salt.
Place 24 large mushroom caps on a baking tray.
Brush with melted margarine.
Stuff with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: macaroni and meat sauce
directions: Brown meat; add
onions and cook about a minute or more. Add tomato sauce, water and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until onion
is
tender,
stirring
occasionally.
Add macaroni long enough for it
to
cook before serving.
Add more water if needed.

title: marzipan strawberries
directions: Mix together; roll small amount into ball, then shape like strawberry.
Roll in red sugar and put cap on.
Recipe makes several dozen.
Freeze well.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix dressing according to package directions.
Layer slices of potatoes and dressing, ending with dressing layer on the top. Sprinkle with onions and radishes just before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add bananas.
Mix.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add nuts.
Put into bread pans that are greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ice box cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, mix well; add vanilla. Sift flour with baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture, add coconut; Mix thoroughly.
Form into rolls 2-inches in diameter.
Chill overnight or up to 2 weeks.
Cut in thin slices. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: pizza burgers(kids' favorite, fun-to-do meal)
directions: Place open buns face up on a cookie sheet.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons sauce on top, then cheese and toppings.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: steve's favorite dressing(for tossed salads)
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour over:

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and mix with remaining ingredients in casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with onion rings and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: celery pork chops
directions: Lay bread in long pan, 9 1/2 x 13-inch.
Brown sausage (drain off fat).
Spread brown sausage on top of bread.
Spread cheese on top of sausage.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk with 1/2 cup milk.
Add tuna, salmon, turkey or chicken (cut in bite size pieces).
Put in casserole.
Add peas.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake 25 minutes in moderate oven.

title: chocolate chip toffee grahams
directions: Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in a jelly roll pan.
Set aside.
In a medium sauce pan, combine butter and sugar. Cook over a medium heat, stirring until butter melts.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Pour over graham crackers, spreading evenly to edges.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cool 5 minutes, separate cookies and transfer to a wax paper lined cookie sheet, using a spatula. Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Store cookies between layers of waxed paper in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: best-ever sweet muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Dip hot, baked muffins in melted margarine and then in sugar.
May add 8 ounces of drained crushed pineapple to batter.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 6-cup salad
directions: Combine and let stand 12 hours.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter in microwave for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over cereal, coating well.
Put confectioners sugar in large plastic bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake well.
Ready to serve.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, cornstarch and pineapple.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Cook cabbage, carrots and green pepper together in small amount of boiling salted water, covered, for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Reserve drippings; saute onion in drippings until browned; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over cooked vegetables and toss well.
Just before serving, sprinkle crumbled bacon over top. Makes 8 servings.

title: joe's hamburgers
directions: Mix together into patties.
Fry in a flat frypan.
Put in hamburger buns with mustard, ketchup, onions and chili sauce. Makes a delicious hamburger.

title: burrito burgers
directions: Combine beans, 2 tablespoons chilies, onions and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Divide into 8 sections.
Shape into 5-inch patties.
On one side of each patty, place slice of cheese.
Fold over, forming semi-circle.
Seal.
Grill over hot coals; turn and cook.
Serve burgers in tortillas.
Top with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and remaining chilies.

title: lime green creamy jello salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and mayonnaise in a small bowl.
In another bowl, mix boiling hot water and lime Jell-O together to dissolve Jell-O.
Pour dissolved Jell-O solution into an oblong Pyrex bowl.
Stir in drained crushed pineapple.
Stir in pecan pieces.
Stir in cottage cheese-mayonnaise mixture.
Chill for several hours in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: milkshake for breakfast
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender; blend for 2 or 3 minutes. Pour into a glass and enjoy a healthy, filling breakfast!

title: chili and rice
directions: In frying pan, brown onions and peppers in small amount of oil.
Set aside.
Brown turkey meat.
Combine with onions and peppers. Then add tomatoes and chili seasonings.
Add to beans. Add rice and simmer until rice is done.

title: apple bread
directions: Blend apple and orange peel in blender.
Add all other ingredients; mix well in mixing bowl. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: martha pafford's chicken and dumplings
directions: Break eggs in bowl; mix in enough flour to absorb liquid. Stir until a thick, stiff batter.
Knead dough.
Roll out on floured wax paper with rolling pin as thin as possible.
Let lay for 1 hour.
Cut in narrow strips, length and width, forming a cube of dough.
Drop into cooked chicken and broth one at a time. Cook on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: french filling for pies, cakes and cream puffs
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Add 1 cup milk.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add egg and 2 cups milk that has been warmed.
Put back on heat and cook 5 minutes, stirring until thick.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla.
When cool, you may add the whipped topping if desired.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Mix and press into pan.

title: orange-almond chicken
directions: Brown hamburger; add taco mix and 1 onion (cut up) and some garlic salt.
Simmer 15 minutes (follow package directions.)
Use corn tortilla shells.
Put oil in pan with paprika.
Heat to hot; add tortilla and put paprika on shell.
After it starts to bubble, turn and add paprika to other side.
Cook 15 to 30 seconds.
Take out; drain on wax paper.
Continue cooking as many as you need. Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, sour cream, etc.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix together pepper, salt, and flour. Coat chicken with seasoned flour. In a heavy bottomed skillet, heat oil. Place chicken breasts in skillet and brown on both sides. Remove chicken from skillet and set aside. To the skillet, add wine and stir until heated. Add juice, stock and mushrooms. Stir to toss, reduce heat and cook for about 10 minutes until sauce is partially reduced. Return the browned chicken breasts to the skillet. Spoon sauce over the chicken. Cover and cook for 5-10 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve over cooked noodles. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: banana split cake
directions: Drain pineapple into deep bowl.
Slice bananas into pineapple juice.
Let sit.
Mix 1 stick softened margarine into graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Refrigerate while mixing other ingredients.
Mix 2 sticks softened margarine and 1 egg in mixing bowl.
Fold in sugar.
Mix for 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Spread pineapple over margarine and sugar layer.
Take bananas out of juice; place over pineapple layer.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and cherries over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil in bowl and beat together.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add alternately with water, continuing to beat
in mixer.
Add pumpkin and nuts. Mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter; add onion and celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Heat at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together well with hands.
Roll in bite-size balls. Freeze.
Bake in oven heated to 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: school style peanut butter delights
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Spread into 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with coconut and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen squares.

title: classic cannoli
directions: In medium bowl, combine cheese, sugar, rind, liqueur and chips. Spoon mixture into pastry bag fitted with a large tip and pipe equal amounts into shells.

title: broiled shrimp and chicken
directions: Alternate chicken, shrimp, tomatoes and green peppers on shish kabob spears; sprinkle with seasoning.
Broil or place all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute carrot and onion in 1 teaspoon oil. Add garlic, oregano, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce. Simmer while you cook and drain spaghetti. Put half the cooked spaghetti in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Pour half the sauce on top. Spread sour cream over this, then spread Parmesan cheese. Layer remaining spaghetti, sauce
and
cheeses,
ending
with Mozzarella. Bake, covered, for 40 minutes; uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes to lightly brown at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: southwestern coating
directions: Cut chicken or pork in small pieces; or slice zucchini.
Mix dry ingredients.
Roll pieces first in dry ingredients, then in egg and water and then again in dry mixture.
Fry in oil until done.

title: microwave carrots
directions: The easiest way to cook carrots is to scrape them first, then toss into a 1 gallon size plastic food bag. Place bag on plate. Microwave on High for about 6 minutes. Cool slightly.
Remove from bag, slice or serve whole.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or one slightly larger.

title: cherry tree pie
directions: Combine pineapple, cherries, sugar, cornstarch, and food coloring.
Cook until clear and thick.
Stir, remove from heat. Let cool at room temperature.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Place in clean crab shells.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Next, spoon melted butter over cracker crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: christmas pie
directions: Bring to boil pie filling, dry jello, sugar, cornstarch, pineapple and juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Add bananas and nuts. Pour in pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix broccoli, onion, raisins and pecans.
Pour mixture over vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook bacon, crumble and add to mixture.
Serve in a clear bowl for looks.

title: one bowl microwave fudge
directions: Put chocolate and milk in large microwave-safe bowl.
Heat on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Remove, stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Next, stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm, cut into small squares to make 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Combine pork, garlic, soy sauce and sherry in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir to coat evenly; let stand 10 minutes.
Blend together apple juice and cornstarch; stir into pork mixture. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes; stir once.
Add onion, broccoli, carrots and pepper; do not stir. Cover and microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add sprouts; cover and microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Toss to mix

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add whipped topping and the

title: red cabbage(from the northwoods inn)
directions: Put ingredients into bowl; mix well.
Let stand several hours or overnight to allow flavors to mellow and slaw to turn deep red.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef and 1/2 package rice.
Make meatballs. Brown meatballs in deep frying pan. Add cream of chicken soup and water to cover meatballs. Add rest of rice.
Stir.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes (until rice is cooked).

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk. Add cheese, green pepper, pimiento and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Pour into shallow casserole.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 servings.

title: party ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Slice rolls in half lengthwise.
Layer ham and cheese.
Put rolls back together and cut individual rolls.
Melt together margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion flakes.
Pour this mixture over rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad ingredients, except mayonnaise and sugar, in a large bowl in the order listed.
Top with the mayonnaise and sugar, which have been mixed together.
(This mixture should cover entire top of salad; make more, if needed.)

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour with next 4 ingredients. Cut in butter with 2 knives or pastry blender, until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Stir in raisins.
Mix vinegar and milk.
Make a well in center of flour mixture.
Add liquid all at once.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board.
Knead gently 8 to 10 times. Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased 8-inch pie plate.
Make an "X" on top with a knife and brush with a little milk for glaze. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 375° and bake 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix pudding as directed.
Into a 4-quart punch bowl, crumble cake.
Top with pudding, pineapple, pie filling and sliced bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use about 3 heaping tablespoons mix with hot water.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder together.
Pour in hot pan.
Then spoon in pie filling.
You can use blueberry, apple, cherry or blackberry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Skin chicken pieces.
Place the pieces, skin side down, in a large shallow baking pan.
(You may wish to line the pan for easy cleaning.)
Baste chicken pieces with barbecue sauce and place in oven.

title: spinach salad with strawberries
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash thoroughly, pat dry and tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine spinach and strawberries in a large salad bowl, tossing gently.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain juice off of asparagus and save.
Spray your casserole dish with Pam or your choice.
Line with cracker crumbs.
Next, put a layer of asparagus spears, then a layer of sliced, boiled eggs.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat the layers and dot the top layer with butter.
Pour the asparagus juice into the casserole just as to where you can see it.
Drop shaved (your favorite) mild cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread maxwell(san francisco)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add next 5 ingredients. Sift together and add the next 4 ingredients.
Bake in a large greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 200°.

title: creme de cacao torte
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, 2/3 cup cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, blending just until combined.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Sprinkle each layer with 1 tablespoon creme de cacao; cool completely.

title: hot spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain, saving 1/2 cup of the liquid. Melt butter.
Add flour; stir well.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add milk and spinach liquid; add seasoning and cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.
Add spinach and blend well.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and heat until hot throughout and starts to brown around edges.
This dish can be made ahead of time and heated when ready to serve.

title: nutty chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift the flour, salt and soda together.
Then blend butter, both sugars, vanilla and water together until fluffy.
Beat in egg. Mix in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Mix half the berries with cornstarch and water.
Add lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Cook about 5 minutes over medium flame; cool.
Place remaining strawberries in pie crust.
Cover with cooked mixture.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve with cream, if desired.
Yields 5 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: mexican dish
directions: Boil
chicken, let cool and debone.
Add other ingredients except
cheese
and
bag of Doritos and mix.
Put in "Pam sprayed"
(greased)
oblong pan or Pyrex.
Add cheese to fully cover
top.
Add rest of Doritos and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bev's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes. Add boiling water. Batter will be thin. Chop up candy bar and stir small chunks in batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and meat in blender. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle cheese and meat on top and press under mixture with the back of a spoon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Quiche will form its own crust.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix and put in a long pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Freezes well.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk; beat.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Mix and pour in desired pie shell. Let set 2 hours.

title: oven fries
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into thick slices (leave peel on potatoes), then into 1/2 inch by 1/2 inch thick strips.
Toss potatoes with oil, spread on a baking sheet. Sprinkle with thyme.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, turning every 10 minutes, until potatoes are brown and crisp.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil and eggs with electric mixer. Then add poppy seed and hot water.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sailor's stew(skipperlabskovs)
directions: Cut the beef into 3/4-inch squares.
Blanch and rinse in cold water.
Chop the onions finely.
Peel and cut up the potatoes. Brown 2 tablespoons butter in a thick bottomed saucepan.
Turn the meat in the butter until just colored.
Add the onions and simmer until transparent.
Add the potatoes, bay leaves and peppercorns and cover with water.
Simmer gently until all the potatoes have mashed up.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
When onion has browned; add soup, curry powder, shrimp and raisins. Heat thoroughly.

title: harvest vegetable scallop
directions: Preheat oven to
In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine carrots, broccoli and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Tuck potato slices into vegetable mixture at an angle.
Dot vegetables evenly with cheese spread.
Pour milk over vegetables.
Sprinkle black pepper and seasoned salt.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 4 to 5 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Knead on a floured surface.
Let rise. Punch down.
Make into 2 loaves or may be made into rolls.
Let rise, then bake at 350° until done and brown.
Butter tops when done.

title: audrey's pound cake(club member: terah smith)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add 7 eggs, one at a time. Add flour all at once; beat well. Pour batter in greased tube pan (do not flour). Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Cool for only 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pork chops
directions: Combine seasonings and rub on chops.
Brown chops in hot fat. Combine bouillon cubes and ginger ale.
Pour on chops and simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook lima beans until just tender and drain.
Combine beans, pimento and onions in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chops on top and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: special k cookies(no bake)
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter; stir in cereal. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: crisp oven fried chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine corn flakes, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dip chicken strips in water and then in corn flake crumbs, pressing the crumbs to make sure they stick.
Place chicken on nonstick baking sheet that has been spread with nonstick cooking spray.
If any crumbs remain, sprinkle evenly over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: rock candy
directions: Boil to hard stage (310°) and remove from heat.
Add flavoring and color.
Stir.
Put on cutting board sprayed with Pam and buttered.
Cut immediately with scissors and put candy pieces in confectioners sugar; shake off excess.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Mix onions with 1 cup cheese and add remaining ingredients. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly at sides.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: heavenly peach angel food cake
directions: Slice cake into 2 layers.
Spread half the preserves between the layers and the remaining half on top.
Frost sides of the cake with whipped cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef stew with dumplings
directions: Brown meat in shortening in Dutch oven.
Add 2 to 4 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Take water and flour and make thickening; blend in stew.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Break stem off. Carefully hand tear lettuce to bite size pieces.
Sizes should not be more than 1.856-inch square.
Rinse and serve chilled.
Garnish with your favorite dressing.
A great feast for all!!

title: elia's punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and thawed concentrates. When ready to serve, add ginger ale, club soda and alcohol (if you wish).
Pour over ice block in punch bowl and garnish with orange, lemon and lime slices.
One-half recipe equals 1 punch bowl full.

title: pastry covered chicken
directions: Thaw pastry sheets as directed on package.
Unfold one sheet and spread out.
Cut into 4 equal sections.
Roll out each section to add about one inch to each side.
In the middle of the rolled out pastry section place 1 teaspoon cream cheese, then place flattened out 1/2 chicken breast.
Roll pastry around chicken and fasten securely.
Place seam side down on lightly greased baking pan.
Just before baking, brush top of pastry with egg and water mixed.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: shake 'n bake
directions: Dip
chicken,
chops
or
fish	in buttermilk or canned milk. Roll
in mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake another 30 minutes.

title: bean and sausage stuffing
directions: In covered 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook sausage and 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Remove cover; reduce heat to low.
Cook sausages until browned, turning often.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut each into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Cook celery and onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine croutons with 1 cup hot water.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Stuffing for a 6 to 8 pound turkey.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple or peach pie with equal or sweet 'n low
directions: Put apple juice in pan.
Add cinnamon, Equal and cornstarch. Cook over medium heat; stir until thick.
Add butter and stir in apples, then spoon into pie shell.
Then put second shell on top and bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Combine cheeses, lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into ball. Sprinkle ball with mixture of chili powder and paprika.
Chill several hours.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix together sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Add paraffin to make glossy effect.
Dip balls in hot mixture and place on waxed paper.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: main dish u.s.a.
directions: Put sliced apples and raisins in baking dish.
Pour water and molasses over top.
Put chops on top; cover.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lime-lemon cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and cool.
Dump ingredients and stir.

title: fat free fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Spray an 8-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, stir together sugar, Sweet One, margarine, Egg Beaters, Butter Buds sprinkles and vanilla.
In a small bowl, stir together dry ingredients; stir into liquid ingredients just until blended.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and cut into squares.
Yields 16 servings.

title: chicken muenster
directions: Filet chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Marinate in beaten egg for 2 hours.
Mix together bread crumbs, parsley and garlic salt.
Roll pieces of chicken in crumb mix.
Fry in salad oil until lightly browned.
Melt butter and put in bottom of large 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Lay chicken on top.
Cover with sliced mushrooms, then cheese slices.
Mix bouillon cubes with boiling water.
Pour over all.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Brown beef
with onion and drain well.
Spread in prepared pie plate. Beat
milk,
eggs,
salt,
pepper
and
Bisquick until smooth. Add
corn; stir well.
Pour mixture over beef; spread evenly. Bake
until knife comes out clean.
Remove from oven. Add cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender; drain.
Beat; add sour cream, cream cheese and butter.
Add salt, pepper and chives. Pour into a casserole.
Melt some butter and put on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put dry ingredients in coffee filter and juices in pot.
Let perk.
Great hot drink for Christmas and aroma for the house.

title: strawberry pecan scones
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.

Add yogurt to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. (Dough will be sticky.) Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; with floured hands, knead 4 to 5 times. Pat dough into an 8-inch circle on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Cut dough into 12 wedges, cutting to but not through dough; make a small slit in center of each wedge. Place 1 teaspoon of strawberry spread on top of each slit; sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 400° for 13 minutes or until golden. Serve warm. Yields 1 dozen. Each has 147 calories and 4.2 g fat.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatine in boiling water.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight or until congealed.
Mix mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Spread on top. Sprinkle cheese on top and serve.

title: bill's deer salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cut into 1 pound strips and roll in foil; twist the end of the foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Take out and cover with water and boil for 1 1/4 hours. Cool and enjoy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
This was colored with green food coloring and used with gold carrots for St.
Patrick's Day, but is good with any fresh vegetable.

title: old-fashion southern democrat pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pie shells or 16 tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Place in roaster; sprinkle with soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes and seasoning.

title: peanut butter play dough(eatable)
directions: Mix equal amounts of peanut butter and nonfat dry milk together to the consistency of play dough, adding more peanut butter or dry milk as needed.

title: barbecue sauce and chicken
directions: Makes enough sauce for basting 2 chickens.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add pineapple juice.
Stir, do not beat! Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: twenty minute chicken creole
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick coating spray and heat on high.
Add chicken strips and cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Reduce heat to medium; add tomatoes and their juice, chili sauce, green pepper, celery, onion, garlic, basil, parsley, crushed red pepper and salt.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or whole wheat pasta.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage together until lightly browned and crumbly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed. Recommend keeping warm in crock-pot.

title: "special k" cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Blend oleo and brown sugar, then add eggs and blend.
Add coconut, chopped nuts, Special K, raisins and vanilla with sifted mixture and blended mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: spicy catfish dip
directions: Combine dressing mix, mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish mustard; mix thoroughly.
Fold in flaked chunks of catfish.
Chill overnight to allow flavors to combine.
Serve with crackers, chips, fresh vegetables or as a spread on toasted party bread. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Flour steak on both sides.
Fry until brown.
Put steak in a deep casserole dish.
Add soup, 1 can of water and Lipton soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 2
hours, turning meat after each hour. "This will melt in your mouth."

title: italian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oven; drain completely.
Pour 1 small jar Prego sauce with mushrooms over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown flour-coated meat in fat; add onion, garlic and drained mushrooms.
Combine seasonings in mushroom liquid (or water if using fresh ones).
Add soup.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Add sour cream and heat just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs. Add rest of ingredients. Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and spices together.
Mix in milk with vinegar.
Mix in melted shortening with molasses. Mix in vanilla and egg, lightly beaten.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: double baked potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 minutes. Mix in all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Measure 2/3 cup dry cake mix and reserve.
In bowl, microwave butter on High 1 minute.
Add remaining cake mix and 1 egg.
Blend well.
Pat mixture into a greased 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Microwave on Medium-high 5 minutes.
Rotate dish a half turn after 2 1/2 minutes.
Combine reserved cake mix, pumpkin, sugar, 2 eggs, orange rind and salt; beat well.
Pour cake batter over first layer.
Sprinkle batter with pecans.
Microwave at Medium-high for 4 minutes.
Cover with wax paper.
Cool before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: helen's christmas fruitcake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine walnuts, raisins, dates and candied fruit.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of flour.
Toss with hands to coat and separate pieces.
Set aside.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Chill all ingredients; pour into ice cream can.
Fill with milk to line on can.
Proceed according to operating instructions.

title: flo eufert's krispie drops
directions: Melt chocolate bark and peanut butter in microwave; add other ingredients. Drop by the tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick each with a fork and wrap individually in aluminum foil.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until done (about 1 hour).
Cut slice from top of each potato and scoop out centers, being careful not to break skin.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Cook at 375°.

title: southern style comb cake
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar until crumbly. Remove 1/2 cup mixture and set aside for topping.
Add remaining ingredients to remaining flour mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining topping over the top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: julia's corn salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving. Garnish with salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: sangria
directions: Put all in a large fruit bowl.
Allow to mellow in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Add a rough red wine and sugar to taste.
Serve over ice.

title: favorite colorful scalloped potatoes
directions: In well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange layers of potato slices, sprinkling each layer with green pepper, carrot and onion.
In saucepan melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and smooth. Add parsley, seasoned with a little salt and pepper to taste. Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered in 350° oven for about 40 minutes, then uncover and bake until potatoes are tender and cheese is delicately browned.
Serves 4.

title: jackie's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, then cool and remove meat from bones.
Use the liquid for the chicken broth.
Use a 2-quart (or larger) casserole dish.
Mix meat with onion, soup, milk and broth.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pancake topping
directions: Blend together and pour topping over hot pancakes.

title: beef tenderloin en croute
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Tie meat with string at 1-inch intervals, if necessary.
Place meat on rack to baking pan.
Roast 45 to 50 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 135°.
Remove from oven.
Cool 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Remove string.
Saute mushrooms in margarine in large skillet 10 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally.
Add cream cheese, bread crumbs, wine, chives and salt; mix well.
Cool.

title: polish kolachky
directions: Cut butter in flour as for pastry.
Crumble yeast in sour cream.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and mix well.
Chill 2-3 hours in refrigerator.
Roll out dough on a board covered with powdered sugar.
Cut into 3 inch squares and fill with fruit filling.
Lap opposite corners to center.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.
Add a dash of powdered sugar on top before serving.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add water and bouillon. Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and pimento (if desired).
Boil 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add Cheez Whiz and cream.
Do not boil!

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cut dates, sprinkle soda over them, add boiling water and let stand.
Cream sugar and butter, add egg.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla, corn flakes and pecans.
Add dates.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spring fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first five ingredients, mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, sprinkle with walnuts and brown sugar. Garnish with mint if desired. Yield 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased roaster or large baking dish.
Add ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered).
Uncover and add cheese.
Continue cooking until cheese has melted and potatoes are lightly brown on top.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Cook until onion is almost clear, approximately 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir and cook for about 2 minutes.
Add soups, water and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
During the last 10 minutes of simmer time, add shrimp or crawfish.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: frozen orange drink
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together in an electric ice cream freezer.
Freeze as you would any ice cream.
Serve.

title: fruit medley
directions: Peel melons; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in large bowl. Add strawberries, peaches and bananas.
Peel and section one of the oranges; add to bowl.
Take second orange and cut in half; squeeze juice over fruit.
Stir gently.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours or overnight, if preferred.

title: cheese-bacon-broccoli squares
directions: Press crescents into cookie sheet to form one large crust. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions, garlic, seasoned salt, pepper and dill weed. Spread over crust.
Top with grated cheese, bacon bits and chopped broccoli flowerets.
Cut in squares and serve cold.

title: egg salad
directions: Cut up eggs coarsely. Add celery, onion, seasoning and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti.
Mix with the egg, milk and Parmesan.
Press into a buttered pizza pan or 10-inch pie plate. Spoon on sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into pizza wedges.
Great lunch for kids.

title: rose's french fresh fries
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in French fry slices.
Beat egg whites a little; add Cajun seasoning.
Mix with potatoes.
Spray Teflon cookie sheet with Pam; add potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender; stir after 10 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dissolve cubes in water.
Add carrots, celery, onions and potatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes and add broccoli and cauliflower. Simmer another 15 minutes; add Velveeta and soup.
Heat until cheese is melted and soup is dissolved, stirring constantly. Season with Tony's.
Can add chicken to this.

title: ham and potato patties
directions: Mix patty ingredients (all ingredients except oil). Form 8 (1/2-inch) patties. Heat 1 teaspoon oil for 4 patties at a time. Cook over medium heat until golden brown on each side, about 5 minutes. Can serve with horseradish sauce.

title: english tea biscuits
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together. Add remaining ingredients to flour mixture and mix until you can form a ball around the bowl.
Roll out on smooth surface 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: lime surprise
directions: Put fruit in saucepan (with juice) and jello.
Bring to boil. Add cold water.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch cake pan and partially gel. Prepare Dream Whip according to instructions.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well.
Fold into jello.
Top with chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon. Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened (spoon drawn through leaves a definite impression).
Reserve remaining 1 cup gelatin at room temperature.

title: tammy's no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, pudding, Coffee-mate, vanilla, Cool Whip and milk.
Line pan with wafers.
Add sliced bananas, then pour filling over this.
Garnish with cookies.
Chill several hours. Serves many.
Great for summer menus.

title: low fat dessert
directions: Prepare each instant pudding with milk.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9 inch dish.
Put chocolate pudding on crackers.
Layer bananas on chocolate pudding.
Spread white chocolate pudding on bananas.
Put strawberries (drained) on white chocolate pudding.
Layer Cool Whip on top.
Top with toasted pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, salt, flour and cheese.
Fold in broccoli.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Cook to desired consistency.
Serve warm or cold.
Freezes well.

title: van family easy peach cobbler
directions: Cook the peaches in 1/4 cup of sugar for 2 minutes or less. Add cinnamon.
Spoon peaches in flat Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, plain flour, egg, margarine, baking powder and vanilla.
Drop by big spoonfuls on top of peaches.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine berries, raisins, sugar, spices and water in a large pan.
Cook 15 minutes until berries pop and mixture thickens. Stir in onion (finely chopped), apple and celery; simmer 15 minutes longer, or until mixture is thick.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add oil, half of parsley, garlic powder, salt, cayenne and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently with butter mixture.
Arrange in skillet or dish in single layer.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg breakfast
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cool.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt, pepper, dry mustard and bread cubes.
Fold in cheese and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (no butter).
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 9 to 10.

title: three-cheese spread
directions: Combine cheeses, Worcestershire sauce and chives or dried onion flakes in a bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Divide mixture into 2 portions.
Shape into balls using floured hands.
Roll in pecans; chill.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone the chicken and layer in casserole dish. Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, almonds, onion and pimentos together and pour over chicken. Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken, soups, chilies, 1 1/2 cups cheese, sour cream and onion together.
Divide the mixture into two bowls.
Use half the mixture to fill the tortillas, rolling them up and placing them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top the 12 rolled tortillas with the remaining half of the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of shredded cheese over the top of the tortillas and chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until well heated.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add margarine and eggs.
Add pineapple and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° (preheated) oven for 45 minutes.

title: party ham delights
directions: Slice
rolls
through
middle (horizontal).
They slice better if	they are partially frozen.
Do not pull apart until ready to serve.
Mix onion, margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy
seed.
Spread on cut surfaces of bread.
Put ham on bottom half
of bread, then cheese on top of ham.	Put top half of bread on.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Cook or freeze. Bake at 350°
until cheese is melted when ready to enjoy with friends.	Cut into sections depending on appetite size.

title: baked potato appetizers
directions: Brush both sides of potato slices with oil; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes on each side or until lightly browned on both sides.
Top potato slices with cheese spread slices and sprinkle with desired topping.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt; serve hot.

title: zucchini bar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly, adding flour last.
Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tenderloin
directions: Marinate all ingredients for 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 450°. Cook for 20 minutes for rare.
Cook for 28 minutes for medium-rare.

title: garden sandwich
directions: Drain and
squeeze
spinach
through strainer.	Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve on rye bread with a slice of Swiss cheese, sunflower
seeds
and sliced mushrooms.
Warm in microwave for 1 minute.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: jean's applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Measure all ingredients into mixing bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high. Pour into pans, bake 60 to 65 minutes. If desired frost when cool.

title: pizza bread
directions: Night before, let
bread rise.
Cook hamburg.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Roll out bread into a rectangle.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and shredded Mozzarella cheese down center.
Spoon hamburg mixture over this, then top with more Mozzarella cheese.
Fold (or lap) sides of bread onto mixture and pinch ends together. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater nugget hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan brown ground beef, onion and celery; drain well.
Stir in soups, garlic powder, pepper and green beans.
Spoon into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
